title: grandma's biscuits
directions: Mix flour, baking powder and salt.
Sift; cut in Crisco.
Add milk gradually until a drop batter is formed.
Put in buttered tins and bake in 400° oven (10 to 15 minutes).

title: granny's home-style fried okra
directions: Place all ingredients in a large bowl and mix; toss with fingers until okra is well coated. Pour into the skillet with the melted shortening and cook, covered, over medium heat until okra is tender and begins to brown. Remove skillet from heat; let cover remain and allow to steam for 10 to 15 minutes before serving. Serves 6 to 8.

title: raisin pie
directions: Bring raisins and water to boil.
Cook 10 to 15 minutes.
Mix and add sugar and cornstarch to cooked raisins.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell; cover with top crust.
Dot with margarine.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Turn oven to 375° and bake until brown.

title: peanut dip for apples
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Stir together ingredients and press onto bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie plate.
Bake for 10 minutes and cool.

title: `big mac' sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients. Great on burgers!

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown beef and sausage until brown; drain grease.
Add cubed cheese; stir until melted with ground beef.
Add sausage and seasonings.
Spread onto bread slices.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: orange raisin quick bread(ultra low-fat, moist and delicious)
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a large bowl, sift together the flour, soda, baking powder, sugar and Molly McButter.
Combine egg product, applesauce, orange juice and zest and mix with electric mixer.
Syir in raisins and cereal.
Gradually add flour mixture to egg mixture and mix thoroughly.
Pour into loaf pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray and bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes. Recipe makes 10 servings.

title: 3-day slaw
directions: Shred or grate cabbage.
Peel onions and slice.
Combine sugar, vinegar, corn oil, mustard and celery seed; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and cool.
Alternate layers of cabbage and onions.
Pour mixture over cabbage and store in a covered container in refrigerator for 3 days before serving.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Chop cranberries, apples and walnuts in blender.
Mix jello and gelatin together in 2-quart casserole dish or loaf pan.
Add hot water.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cut apples and oranges as putting them in.
Stir gently; put in fridge for 1/2 hour and stir again.
Allow to set and serve.
This is very good for the holidays.

title: low calorie stuffed baked potatoes
directions: Fresh chives may be used in place of dried chives.

title: no bake fruit cake
directions: Dump all ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Using hands, mix well.
Press in angel food pan.
Cover and refrigerate for at least 2 days before serving.

title: cobbler
directions: Spread filling in 13 x 9 pan. Cream butter; add dry cake mix and eggs and mix well. Spoon over filling. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until golden brown. Cut into squares.

title: break'fast pizza
directions: In greased 10 x 13-inch pan, crumble bread.
Pour beaten eggs mixed with a little milk over bread.
Layer meat and onions.
Top with cheese.
Put mushroom soup in dollops over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
This can be topped with cream gravy.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix the bacon and vegetables.
Pour off juices and save.
Put cornbread into vegetables (crumble).
Mix mayonnaise and juice together.
Pour over salad.

title: barbecue pork
directions: In crock-pot, cook roast with onion and garlic on low overnight.
Pour liquid off pork, take pork off bone and discard fat.
Add barbecue sauce to meat; cook on low for 4 hours, stirring 2 or 3 times.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread sugar cookie dough on pizza pan and bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes until edges turn brown.
Mix cream cheese, Cool Whip and powdered sugar.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix in small saucepan the juice, cornstarch, lemon juice and water; cook until thickened.
Arrange fruit in attractive pattern on cheese mixture, then spoon glaze over fruit.

title: miniature shrimp quiche
directions: Beat butter and cream cheese at medium speed until well blended.
Stir in flour and salt.
Cover dough and refrigerate for one hour.
Shape chilled dough into 36 one-inch balls.
Place in ungreased muffin pans, shaping each ball into a shell.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: mashed potatoes with cheese
directions: Add sour cream and Philadelphia cream cheese to mashed potatoes and whip together until desired taste is obtained.
Thin with half and half cream until desired texture is obtained.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Put some yellow shredded cheese on top.
Bake one hour at 350°.

title: crab and cheese bites(appetizer)
directions: Mix oleo, cream cheese, crabmeat and Cheez Whiz.
Spread on English muffin halves.
Put in freezer until firm enough to cut into wedges, approximately 1 hour.
Remove from freezer and cut into wedges, about 4 per half.
Refreeze in plastic bag.
When ready to use, remove amount to be used and broil until golden brown.
Cheese Bites can be kept in freezer for a few months.
Add horseradish or use jalapeno Cheez Whiz for a spicier taste or serve with shrimp cocktail sauce on top of each wedge.
Serves 8.

title: spiced tea(microwave)
directions: Combine all ingredients until well blended.
Store mix in an airtight container.

title: fluffy rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well. Let rise 30 minutes.
Mix again.
Spoon into greased muffin tins and let rise 30 minutes again.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 400°.

title: peanut bar cookies
directions: Stir together flour & brown sugar; cut in cold butter until mixture is crumbly.
Stir in 1/2 cup peanut butter chips.
Press mixture on bottom of greased 12 x 9 baking pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Meanwhile combine condensed milk, egg and vanilla; stir in remaining chips and nuts.
Spread evenly over baked crust. Bake 35 minutes at 350°. Cool completely in pan.
Cut in squares.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Combine cukes, onions and salt.
Soak 3 hours.
In pan, warm vinegar and sugar.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Drain cukes and add to vinegar mixture.
Ladle into freezer plastic containers and freeze.
Defrost and serve chilled.
Makes 1 1/2 quarts.

title: cheese ball
directions: Place Milnot and Blue cheese in blender; process on medium. Gradually add Cheddar cheese and flavorings.
Process on high.
Add cream cheese; continue processing until mixture is smooth.
Shape into ball and refrigerate overnight.
Wrap in foil or wax paper. About 30 minutes before serving, roll ball in pecan-parsley mixture, if desired.

title: diabetic blackberry jam
directions: Place crushed berries into large kettle; add sweetener and stir well.
Boil rapidly, stirring constantly.
After mixture has thickened, pour into hot jars leaving head space of 1/4-inch. Adjust caps, processing in boiling water for 15 minutes.
One tablespoon has 10 calories.

title: fast paced chicken
directions: Place chicken in a glass 9-inch baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Refrigerate 8 to 24 hours. Preheat oven to 350° and bake 1 hour.
Good served with rice and a steamed squash medley.
Serves 4.

title: no peek cake
directions: Bake cake as directed in 2 round cake pans. Split each layer in half horizontally. Mix sour cream, sugar and coconut. Reserve 1 cup for icing. Spread the rest in equal amounts between the layers. Mix reserved amount with Cool Whip. Ice cake. Store in airtight container in refrigerator for 3 days. Serve.

title: grandma's sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy. Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition. Set aside 2 tablespoons flour. Add rest of flour to creamed mixture. Add sour cream and mix well. Combine 2 tablespoons flour with baking soda, then add to mixture.
Add vanilla and almond extract and blend thoroughly. Turn into 10-inch greased and floured tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: milk chocolate brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Grease bottom of 9 x 13 pan. In large bowl, mix the thawed whipped topping, eggs and vanilla until smooth. Stir in nuts. Spread mixture into pan. Sprinkle chocolate chips on top. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes or until tooth pick comes out clean. Do not overbake. Cool and slice.

title: apricot-glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Place sweet potatoes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish and set aside.
In a saucepan, combine sugar, cornstarch, salt and cinnamon; stir in apricot nectar, water and orange peel.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook and stir 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat, stir in butter and pecans.
Pour over sweet potatoes. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until heated through.
Yield:
8 to 10 servings.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
Break oranges into pieces.
Let set overnight.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In 8 x 8-inch pan, melt butter or margarine.
Remove melted butter from heat, add cocoa and stir until well blended.
Add eggs, one at a time, beat well.
Stir in vanilla, flour and salt.
Do not overbeat.
Fold in nuts and spread on prepared pan.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until toothpicks inserted in center comes out clean.

title: pepparkakor cookies from kirsten's cookbook
directions: Sift together into bowl the measured flour, baking soda, cinnamon, ginger and cloves.
In larger bowl, stir sugar and softened butter.
Add the egg, maple syrup and water to the butter and sugar; beat until fluffy.
Stir the dry ingredients into the mixture, 1 cup at a time, mixing well after each addition.
Chill the dough in refrigerator 1 hour.

title: peas and pasta
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Add cut garlic or garlic powder to oil (not garlic salt!).
Add peas to oil and garlic.
Salt and pepper. Serve over cooked pasta.
Top with Parmesan cheese.

title: barley casserole
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in oleo.
Combine with barley and liquid in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: hamburger barbecue
directions: Chop celery, onions and pepper.
Brown ground meat.
Add celery, onions and green pepper until soft.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder to taste.
Drain fat.
Mix ketchup, water, brown sugar and mustard.
Pour over meat.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes. Serve on hamburger rolls with potato chips.
Great crowd pleaser!

title: ho ho cake
directions: Cook the flour and milk and stir continuously until thick, then cool.
Blend together the sugar, margarine and shortening.
Combine with above milk mixture and beat 3 to 4 minutes until fluffy. Spread on cooled cake.
Refrigerate until set.

title: willy's blue cheese dressing
directions: Blend together very well with wire whip.
Refrigerate overnight before using.
Makes 1 quart.

title: pineapple torte
directions: Make sauce of cream, sugar, flour, pineapple and vanilla. Cook until thick.
Put layer of crushed wafers in bottom of 8 x 12-inch pan or dish.
Add sauce, then remaining wafers on top. Refrigerate.
This can be made a day ahead.
Serves 10.
Top with whipped cream.

title: aunt jan's baking powder biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add milk; just enough to hold dough together.
Pat 1/2-inch thick on floured board.
Cut and brush with milk.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 12 to 16 small biscuits.

title: butterfinger bars
directions: Cream together the butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Add quick oats.
Place in well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan; pack down. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: pineapple, nut, cheese salad
directions: Beat cream cheese at room temperature. Add Equal and beat well. Blend in Cool Whip, pineapple and pecans. Refrigerate.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Put in crock-pot, Ro-Tel, cheese soup, tomatoes, tomato sauce and cabbage.
Cook beef until done.
Saute onion and bell pepper until brown.
Add all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook 1 hour at high temperature.

title: tuna noodle casserole
directions: Mix in 2-quart casserole dish.
Combine soup and milk.
Stir in noodles, peas, tuna and pimento.
Cover; microwave on High for 9 minutes or until hot, stirring twice during heating.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Cream 1 cup butter and sugar together in bowl. Beat in 4 eggs and pumpkin.
Sift next 5 ingredients into batter, mixing well. Add 3/4 cups water, vanilla and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into 2 large loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate 'n' oat bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine flour, oats, sugar and margarine, mix well.
Reserving 1/2 cup oats mixture, press remainder on bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes. Pour milk over crust; sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips.
Top with oat mixture; press down firmly.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown; cool.
Cut into bars, store covered at room temperature.

title: meat balls
directions: Mix ground beef, meat tenderizer, garlic powder, salt and pepper.
Roll into walnut-size balls.
Brown in skillet on medium heat, covered.
Drain fat and add water, ketchup and about 3 tablespoons brown sugar.
Simmer about 30 minutes.
(If sauce is too watery, add more ketchup.)

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Put together yeast and 1 1/2 cups warm water.
Let rise, then add to other mixture as soon as the other mixture is lukewarm. Then use bread flour (I use Action) to thicken.
Let rise like other bread.

title: watergate salad
directions: Blend together pudding and Cool Whip.
Add pineapple (with juice).
Add nuts and mix thoroughly.

title: yogurt dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a blender on medium speed for 5 seconds.

title: chicken breast
directions: Mix all the ingredients together and pour over chicken.
Bake in 400° oven until nice and brown, about an hour and a half to two hours.

title: barbecue round steak for microwave
directions: Cut round steak into serving pieces.
Place in a 3-quart glass casserole dish.
Combine remaining ingredients; pour over steak. Refrigerate for several hours.
Microwave, covered, on power level 4 for 50 minutes.

title: cheese frosted cauliflower
directions: Cook cauliflower, leaving whole.
Drain well.
Place it in a shallow pan and frost with mayonnaise, mixed with mustard. Sprinkle on cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 10 minutes.
Simple and fantastic.

title: busy day frosting
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Bring to a boil and spread on hot cake. Brown under low broiler heat and watch closely.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add ice water, vanilla, nuts and flour.
Shape into finger length rolls.
Bake at 300° for 30 minutes on cookie sheet.
Cool, roll in powdered sugar.

title: shrimp fried rice
directions: Heat frying pan or wok, add oil and cook onions until golden brown.
Add mushrooms and water chestnuts and cook one minute. Stir in cold rice, mix well and cook an additional 2 minutes.
Add sugar, eggs, soy sauce and shrimp.
Cook until heated through and golden brown in color.
Garnish with chopped green onions.

title: salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, combine the beef, egg, onion, milk, crumbs, salt and pepper.
Shape into 4 oval patties.
Fry in a skillet over medium heat until done.
Remove patties and keep warm.
Add gravy and water to the skillet.
Heat 3 to 5 minutes.
Serve over patties.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine eggs and milk well and add cracker crumbs.
Set aside until liquid is absorbed.
Add remaining ingredients except cheese to cracker crumbs mixture, stirring well.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese while hot.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Boil sugar, water and Karo until it spins like threads.
Keep folding in egg whites while you pour in sugar mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts.

title: wedding punch
directions: Mix all.
Float sherbet in punch bowl if desired.

title: yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Sift dry ingredients into large bowl, add shortening,
yeast mixture and water.
Mix and knead for 10 minutes.
Put to rise in a warm place.
In 1 hour punch down.
Let rise another hour and make loaves, rolls, etc. and place in greased pans.
Let rise till double in size and bake at 375 -425° depending on size of bread.

title: lasagne
directions: In large pot, heat tomato sauce and seasoning.
Simmer about 1 hour.
Add ground beef.
In separate pot heat noodles to boiling for 7 minutes.
Drain.
Place 3 noodles lengthwise in 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Add sauce to cover.
Sprinkle on both cheeses. Repeat until ingredients are all used.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until top is bubbly and golden.

title: hamburger and potato surprise
directions: Divide hamburger into 4 parts; shape into thin patties.
Place each patty in center of 10-inch square of foil.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover with slices of potato and onion.
Add carrot slices.
Wrap foil securely around hamburger.
Bake in oven at 375° to 425° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: low-fat apricot chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Shake chicken in a plastic bag filled with flour and salt until chicken is coated.
Place chicken in a single layer in a shallow baking pan.
Bake for 25 minutes. Combine apricot preserves, mustard and yogurt.
Spread apricot mixture on chicken and bake for 30 minutes more or until done.

title: jewish nut cookies
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, cocoa, salt and nuts. Spread on greased 11 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. While still hot, add Eagle Brand condensed milk over top and smooth out.
Put coconut on top and bake additional 15 minutes at 350°. Cool completely and ice with Pillsbury chocolate fudge icing.

title: onion soup
directions: In a heavy 3-quart saucepan, heat oil and saute onions for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Lower heat, cover pan and steam for 10 minutes.
Then add bouillon, bay leaf, thyme, salt, pepper and wine.
Simmer for an additional 10 minutes.
Place soup in 4 deep ovenproof bowls and top each with a slice of toasted bread. Sprinkle with grated cheese and place under broiler until cheese is bubbly.
Makes 4 servings.

title: egg custard
directions: Separate 3 egg whites.
Beat the 3 egg yolks and 2 whole eggs with sugar and vanilla. Add the milk, then add melted margarine. Fold in egg whites. Beat until smooth.
Pour in unbaked pie shell and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and drain, then add garlic, basil, salt, tomatoes and tomato paste.
Simmer for 30 minutes in covered skillet.
Cook noodles by directions on box.
Combine cottage cheese, Parmesan, parsley, eggs, salt and pepper.
Mix in mixer.
Place half of noodles in dish and spread with half cottage cheese filling. Place sliced Mozzarella and then half the meat mixture, repeat this again.
Bake at 375° for half an hour and let stand 10 minutes before cutting.

title: green or red peppers(how to freeze)
directions: Wash peppers; remove tops, stems and seeds. Blanch in boiling water for 2 minutes. (Blanching is not necessary, but makes peppers easier to pack.) Cool and drain.

title: scalloped rice
directions: Mix all ingredients, except light cream.
Spoon rice mixture into 1 1/2-quart shallow casserole dish.
Pour light cream on rice mixture.
Bake at 350°, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until set.

title: baozi (chinese dumplings)
directions: Cook and crumble meat.
Squeeze thawed spinach to remove water.
Mix spinach, meat, soy sauce and sesame oil to taste. Stack 2 biscuits and flatten to 1/4-inch round.
Put spoonful of filling in center and pinch edges together.
Place on rack over (not in) boiling water and steam 15 minutes.
Makes 15; good hot or cold.

title: quick party spread
directions: In medium bowl, beat the cream cheese and milk until smooth. Beat in soup mix until blended.
Cover; chill until ready to serve, at least 2 hours.
Makes 1 1/4 cups.

title: lemon icebox fluff
directions: Pour milk in bowl and partly freeze.
Line 9 x 13-inch pan with cracker crumbs.
Separate eggs.
In one bowl, beat egg yolks with sugar and 3 tablespoons lemon juice.
In a separate bowl, beat evaporated milk until thick and add remaining lemon juice. In third bowl, beat egg whites until stiff.
To assemble, fold yolk mixture into egg whites then fold in milk mixture.
Put in 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze.

title: sweet potato puffs
directions: Whip together sweet potatoes, butter, milk and pepper.
Beat in egg yolks, whip egg whites with salt until stiff.
Fold into sweet potatoes.
Pile into buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes, or until puffed and top surface is lightly browned.
Serves 6.

title: leprechaun cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to box directions.
Bake in 13 x 9-inch pan for only 15 minutes; let cool.
Soften cream cheese; beat in milk and pudding; pour over cake.
Spread pineapple over pudding mixture.
Spread with whipped cream; sprinkle with nuts. Enjoy.

title: avocado mayonnaise
directions: Combine avocado, chili pepper, parsley, garlic and scallions in a food processor.
Process to a puree.
Gradually add the oil and beat well.
Add the lime juice.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Serve sauce with either fish or on cocktail toast. Makes abut 1 1/2 cups.

title: rice cereal crust
directions: Mix ingredients well and press into bottom and sides of greased 8-inch pie plate.
Chill well and fill.

title: diabetic jelly
directions: All ingredients should be mixed well.
Boil the mixture gently for 5 minutes.
Let cool and then pour into sterilized containers and store in the refrigerator.
This recipe does contain natural sugar so you will need to figure the calorie and sugar count for it.

title: swiss vegetable medley
directions: Combine vegetables, soup, 1/2 cup cheese, sour cream, 1/2 can onion rings, salt and pepper.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 30 minutes.
Top with remaining cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, for 5 minutes.

title: club chicken casserole
directions: In saucepan, melt butter, blend in flour.
Add milk, broth and 1/2 cup of water.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Add rice, chicken, mushrooms, green pepper, pimento and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes or until hot.
If desired, top with 1/4 cup toasted slivered almonds.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: blueberry crunch
directions: In a 13 x 9-inch baking dish, layer as listed:
berries, sugar, pineapple, cake mix, sugar, butter or margarine and nuts. Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes.

title: flank steak
directions: Slice steak as thin as bacon strips.
Put bacon on top of steak strips and roll.
Secure with a toothpick.
Saute steak rolls in olive oil until all sides are browned.
In a roasting pan combine broth and 1 1/2 cans water and mushrooms; add flank steak. Bake at 400° for about 1 hour.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Shape and put in baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour over meat loaf.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
May double recipe for 2 large and 1 small loaf pan.
Use less batter for smaller pans.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in a food processor or blender and chill until thick. Serve with desired fresh vegetables.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Take 1/2 of mixture, place dish in refrigerator.
When formed, cover with sour cream.
Place other half of mixture when jellied on top of bottom layer.

title: mandarin orange pineapple cake
directions: Beat well.
Bake in 3 layers, cool.

title: nanny's krispie pork chops
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Wash pork chops.
Dip in butter, then roll in Rice Krispies.
Place on a baking sheet lined with foil. Drip leftover butter over chops.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes.
Rice Krispies will get golden brown.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion and garlic powder.
Add ketchup, mustard and A.1. sauce to meat until warm.
Pour into a casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Cut biscuits into quarters, arrange on top of cheese. Bake in preheated 350° oven until biscuits are golden brown.
Kids love it.

title: strawberry jello salad
directions: Pour 1/2 the mixture in bowl and let it congeal. Spread 1 cup sour cream over it and sprinkle with pecans.
Pour the other half of the Jell-O mixture over it.

title: blushing orange coolers
directions: Combine 1st three ingredients, stir to dissolve sugar.
May refrigerate covered up to 1 week. To serve, add club soda to juice mixture. Serve over crushed ice. Garnish with orange rind curls and fresh cranberries. Yields 4 cups.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 400° for one hour.

title: fireside coffee
directions: Put in jar and give as gift.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Combine potatoes (mashed as usual) with cream cheese and mix well.
Add remaining ingredients and place in casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9-inch pan.
Preheat oven at 350°.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix all ingredients except apples and chips.
Fold in apples; pour into pan.
Sprinkle chips on top. Bake 1 hour.

title: arizona quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Set out pie shell to thaw.
Beat eggs with milk and salt.
Add cheese and chilies; mix well and pour in pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Turn oven down to 300°. Bake for 45 to 50 minutes or until set.

title: beef noodle bake
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions and drain.
In skillet, cook beef, onions and green peppers until meat is brown and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat.
Stir in tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Blend together cottage cheese and cream cheese until fluffy. Spoon the noodles into a greased 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish. Spread cheese mixture over noodles.
Pour meat sauce over all.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until heated through (30 or 40 minutes).

title: easy rolls
directions: Mix together well.
Looks like pancake batter.
Butter muffin pans and bake at 325° until brown.

title: microwave fudge
directions: In microwave, in 1 1/2-quart casserole, stir powdered sugar, cocoa, salt, milk and vanilla together.
Mixture will be thick, so you may only partially blend together.
Put sliced butter on top, centering it on mixture.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes.
Dish will feel warm on the bottom.
Stir vigorously until smooth. Blend in the nuts.
Pour into wax paper lined 8 x 8-inch square pan.
Chill well and cut into squares.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Melt butter in a large baking dish.
Add all other ingredients except shrimp and mix well.
Add shrimp and mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: shrimp in wine sauce
directions: Combine water, clam juice and bay leaf in large saucepan; bring to boiling.
Add shrimp.
After mixture comes to boil again, lower heat; simmer 3 minutes or until shrimp are firm tender. Drain, reserving cooking liquid.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken and pour into mixing bowl.
Add all ingredients except cheese.
Mix together and pour into 9 x 12-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle grated cheese on top and bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serves 6. You may want to prepare your chicken ahead of time and freeze to make this a quick meal.

title: crabmeat dip
directions: Blend cream cheese with mayonnaise.
Add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: oatmeal cake
directions: Mix oats and boiling water and set aside.
Cream together next four ingredients and beat well, then add dry ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured pan for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
When done, pour cake topping on and put under broiler until coconut browns.

title: peanut butter tandy takes
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Add milk and flour, alternately.
Pour into 17 x 11-inch pan (cookie sheet).
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and immediately spread 3/4 to 1 cup creamy peanut butter on top.
Place in refrigerator until cooled.
When cooled, melt one (8 ounce) Hershey bar and 1 tablespoon of oil.
Spread on top of cake.

title: nacho dip
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in bean dip, chili seasoning mix, hot sauce, parsley, taco sauce, 3/4 cup Cheddar cheese and 3/4 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Spoon mixture into lightly greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with remaining 1/2 cup Cheddar cheese and 1/2 cup Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Serve hot with tortilla chips.
Yields about 3 1/2 cups.

title: potato salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put in a large bowl.

title: collard greens with tomatoes, onion and garlic
directions: Start the bacon frying in a large pot.
Fry for about 5 minutes, add water and turn up the flame.
Bring to a boil, then lower the flame.
Simmer for about 1 1/2 hours, until the liquid has been reduced to about 3 cups.
Add the greens to the pot. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Remove the cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Heat oil in a cast-iron skillet.
Add onions and garlic; saute for 10 minutes or until onions wilt.
Add the tomatoes, red pepper flakes, salt and pepper.
Mix and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Place rice in dish.
Stir in soup and Cheez Whiz.
Cut up frozen broccoli (uncooked) and mix with rice mixture.
Cover loosely.
Microwave 15 minutes on High (regular oven for 30 minutes at 350°).

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour into hot, greased skillet and bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.

title: squash casserole
directions: Pour milk over crushed bread or cracker crumbs and set aside. Mix all other ingredients together well, then add milk and crumb mixture.
Place in greased casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes.

title: bunuelos(fried bread)
directions: Combine
flour,
salt and baking powder; mix well.
Add fat and
mix.
Add water and mix.
Knead with hands real well. Roll into
small round shapes or cut into small squares.
Fry in hot cooking oil or vegetable shortening.
Delicious.
Serve hot. Delicious with honey.

title: "marshmallow pavlova slice"
directions: Lightly grease 15 x 10 x 2-inch ovenproof baking dish and dust with cornstarch (coat well).
Beat egg whites in large, deep bowl until greatly increased in bulk and soft peaks form.
Add 2 1/2 cups sugar gradually and beat well after each addition until thoroughly dissolved.
Add vanilla essence and vinegar and beat for extra minute.
(Mixture should be glossy with firm peaks.)

title: almond biscotti
directions: Mix the first 8 ingredients in large mixing bowl, then add flour and almonds until well blended.
Separate dough into 3 parts; roll each into a "rope."
Place on greased cookie sheet and flatten slightly.
Brush with egg and water mixture.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes, until center is slightly firm.
Cool slightly. Slice diagonally with sharp knife.
Recipe can be doubled.

title: spicy beef strips
directions: Cut round steak into 2 x 1/2-inch strips.
Set aside.
Heat cooking oil in a large wok.
Add garlic and stir-fry until browned. Remove garlic.
Add the round steak strips, half at a time, and stir-fry until browned.
Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water. Add to wok with all the ingredients.
Stir to mix.
Cover and simmer 25 to 30 minutes or until meat is tender.
Serve over hot fluffy rice.
Serves 6.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in a large bowl.
Add vegetable oil, sugar, grated zucchini and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon, baking soda and salt and mix.
Add raisins and chopped nuts and mix. Pour into a greased loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes (test).

title: pineapple dip
directions: Place cottage cheese and lemon juice in electric blender and blend until smooth.
Add ginger and honey and place in a serving bowl.
Spear pineapple chunks with toothpicks and set in the dip or arrange around bowl.

title: southern biscuits
directions: Sift together all the dry ingredients and work in the shortening.
Add the liquid to make a soft dough, then roll it out on a lightly floured board to a thickness of 1/2-inch.
With a biscuit cutter, cut the dough before putting it into a greased pan and baking it in a hot oven at 425°, for 15 minutes.

title: banana split smoothie
directions: Put all ingredients in a blender and mix until thick.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Beat in eggs.
Add flour, soda, salt and spices.
Combine applesauce and syrup; add to butter mixture. Fold in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 greased 8 x 8-inch pans.
Bake at 300° for about 1 hour.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots approximately 7 minutes.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients and pour over carrots.
Keeps for weeks!
Very tasty.

title: chicken salad
directions: Note:
One 12.5 ounce can chicken can be used.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Mix 1 cup flour with dry ingredients.
Mix 1 cup flour and liquid ingredients.
Mix well.
Make 2 balls and chill.
Make small balls and roll in granulated sugar.
Place on ungreased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: southern pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pecans last.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, and eggs.
Add vanilla and vinegar.
Fold in coconut, raisins, and nuts.
Bake in unbaked pie shell at 300° for 40-45 minutes.

title: chilli
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain.
Add flour.
Add tomato juice, tomato sauce and chilli beans.
Put into a slow cooker and heat 3 to 4 hours.

title: springtime-simple strawberry pie(diet pie)
directions: Combine gelatin, pudding and water in a kettle.
Cook on high until thickened; stir several times.
Cool some.
Add strawberries and gently blend.
Turn into prepared graham cracker crust or into a purchased graham cracker crust.
Chill 3 to 3 1/2 hours. Garnish with whipped cream for serving.
Serves 6.

title: beef tips on rice
directions: Cut meat into 1/2 to 1-inch cubes.
Season with seasoned salt. Place in a large gumbo pot.
Just cover meat with water; cook until tender.
Mix cornstarch with a little water.
Pour slowly into hot broth, stirring constantly until desired thickness. Simmer for 20 to 25 minutes.
Add Kitchen Bouquet until desired color.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Pat cookie dough into an ungreased 14-inch pizza pan.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes, or until brown.
Cool.

title: cheesy meat loaf
directions: Cook onion and green pepper in boiling water until tender; drain.
Stir in tomato sauce, eggs, cheese, bread crumbs, salt, pepper and thyme.
Add ground meats, mixing well.
Shape into loaf in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: bavarian apple cheesecake
directions: In a medium mixer bowl, beat the first 1/3 cup sugar, margarine, shortening and 1/4 teaspoon vanilla on medium speed of an electric mixer until combined.
Blend in flour and salt until crumbly.
Pat into bottom of a 9-inch spring-form pan.
Set aside.

title: crab pizza
directions: Blend cream cheese and lemon juice, then add onion, worcestershire and mayonnaise. Shape into round 9 inch shallow dish or flat plate. Top
with chili sauce. Just before serving, top with crab and one layer of parsley. Serve with crackers.

title: parsley-cheese toasts
directions: Cut bread in 3/4-inch slices to within 1/4-inch of bottom of loaf.
Blend butter, parsley and garlic powder.
Spread in between slices and on top.
Put slices of cheese between bread slices. Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes or until cheese has melted and bread is brown and crusty.

title: mock southern cheese cake
directions: Cream together the cream cheese and sugar.
Blend with Cool Whip; pour into crust.
Refrigerate for about 1 hour.
Top with fresh fruit or canned pie filling.

title: tommy's pizza burritos
directions: Place 1 tortilla on microwavable plate; spoon sauce over tortilla to your liking.
Sprinkle with cheese and top with favorite toppings.
Microwave on High for 1 1/2 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted; watch carefully and remove from microwave. Let cool for few minutes; roll up like burrito and eat.
Makes 10 if using small tortillas.
A fast and easy snack that is tasty and fun for kids to make.

title: ham souffle
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
Place 8 slices in ungreased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Glass is good.
Cover with 8 slices cheese and cut up ham.
Place remaining bread on top.
Mix well the eggs, milk, mustard (can by dry) and seasoned salt.
Pour mixture over bread.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: biscotti red wine
directions: In a large bowl
make
a
well	with
flour.
Place all ingredients in middle and
mix
flour
into
center until well mixed.
Knead dough on
a
lightly floured surface with palms. Cut dough into small pieces
and
roll	into a 8-inch rope and pinch ends together to
form
small circles.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: rhubarb preserves
directions: Cut rhubarb into small pieces. Add the white sugar. Cover tightly in a large kettle (deep pan with a lid).
Let stand 4 hours or until some liquid has formed.
Remove cover and place kettle on low heat.
As juice completely covers rhubarb, heat may be turned up.
Bring to a boil (hard boil) for 3 minutes. Remove from heat. Skim off foam. Stir in the strawberry gelatin (6 ounces).
Pour into glasses.
Cover with paraffin.
May be kept in the refrigerator or freezer.

title: rich potato soup
directions: Melt 1 tablespoon margarine in a large pot.
Saute onion and celery in margarine.
Add 3 1/2 cups water and then add potatoes, carrots and cabbage (if desired).
Add chicken bouillon.
Cook until veggies are tender (may need to add water).

title: turtle cake
directions: Combine cake mix, butter and 1/2 cup Carnation milk.
Mix well and spread 1/2 on bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake for 5 to 6 minutes at 350°.
Melt caramels with 1/2 cup Carnation milk and pour over baked cake.
Add all pecans and chocolate chips on caramels.
Spread rest of cake batter on top. Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with cheese. Return to oven until cheese is melted.
(Leave cheese out if not desired.)

title: rave revue coconut cake
directions: Blend cake mix, pudding, water, eggs and oil.
Beat at medium speed 4 minutes.
Stir in coconut and nuts.
Pour into 2 or 3 (9-inch) greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Cool in pans 15 minutes.
Remove from pans and cool on rack. Frost with Coconut Cream Frosting.

title: grits casserole
directions: Cook grits, margarine and water together until grits are done. Add Velveeta cheese and Tabasco; let cool.
Add eggs and garlic salt.
Bake at 375° for 40 minutes.
Serves many.
Good to freeze.

title: potato casserole
directions: Mix all together and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.
Can be prepared ahead of time and frozen.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cook vermicelli as directed on package. Set aside.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix together the first 7 ingredients in a very large bowl. Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth. Divide into 3 loaf pans, well-greased on bottom.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until done.
Freezes well.

title: mary's sweet pickled peppers
directions: Wash, stem and seed peppers.
Cut in long wedge pieces.
Pack into jars.
Cover with boiling water.
Let stand 5 minutes, pour off.
Add garlic, salt and oil to each jar.
Boil vinegar, sugar and water for 5 minutes.
Pour over peppers and seal.
Be sure no oil is on jar rims or jars will not seal properly.

title: buster bar
directions: Mix cookie ingredients together and press in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer ice cream, peanuts and then hot fudge.
Keep in freezer until ready to serve.

title: aztec soup
directions: Heat bouillon and chilies to a simmer.
Place sliced avocado and about 1/3 cup tortilla chips in each bowl.
Add broth and pepper.
Makes 6 cups.
Serves 4.

title: baked stuffed clams
directions: Melt butter with herbs on low heat for 20 minutes.
Meanwhile, chop celery, green pepper, onion and clams.
Add that to the bread crumbs and herbed butter.
Mix thoroughly.
Fill the clam shells and top with bacon.
Bake in a preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Fills 15 to 20 large clam shells.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Heat milk and butter (keep hot).
Beat eggs until lemon colored (2 minutes).
Gradually add sugar.
Beat in medium 4 to 5 minutes. Add flour and stir with a spoon.
Add hot mixture and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix margarine, eggs and sugar; add milk.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Last, add apples and raisins.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Good with caramel icing or without any.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in lightly salted water according to package directions.
Drain well.
Put broccoli, butter and cheese back in pan in which you've cooked the broccoli.
Cook over very low heat until butter and cheese melt, mixing well.
Put in casserole dish. Top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until casserole is bubbly.

title: stew beef
directions: Mix soups together in large Dutch oven. Add sherry. Bake covered at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.

title: number 1 german slaw
directions: Cover the first 3 ingredients and let stand for 15 minutes. Combine the remaining ingredients and boil.
Pour over the cabbage and let stand.

title: sweet potato biscuits
directions: Knead ingredients together; roll into biscuits.
Bake for 20 minutes at 425°.
Yields 12 to 14 biscuits.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, except flavoring and poppy seed, with mixer.
Add almond flavoring and poppy seed.
Pour batter into a buttered tube pan, which has been dusted with a mixture of sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: dot's chocolate cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients and syrup.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: lemon-cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together shortening, oleo, and cream cheese.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add lemon flavoring.
Fold in flour, reserving 1/4 cup.
Mix 1/4 cup flour with grated cheese and add to cake mixture.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan.
Place in a cold oven.
Bake at 275° for 1 1/2 hours.
Do not open oven door while cake is baking. Remove and cool for 10 minutes.

title: sweet-sour meat balls
directions: Mix meat, crumbs, egg and salt and roll into small balls. Broil in oven or pan. Fry on top of stove until meat balls are brown.
Drain meat balls. Saute' pepper and onion in butter until tender and add remaining ingreds. to make sauce. Add meat balls, cover and simmer 30 min. Yield 6 servings.
Recipe doubles nicely and may be frozen.

title: hawaiian salad
directions: Combine ingredients and chill.
Garnish with lettuce leaves.

title: banana split cake
directions: Combine vanilla wafer crumbs and melted margarine.
Press into 8 x 13-inch baking pan.

title: apple dip
directions: Leave cream cheese on counter until soft.
Place softened cream cheese in a bowl.
Add Kraft Jet-Puffed Marshmallow Creme.

title: shower punch
directions: Mix water, sugar and Kool-Aid. Add both grapefruit juices. Chill.
This is better if you will mix the ingredients all except the ice cream the day before.
This will cause the flavors to blend together.
When ready to serve add ice cream.
Add just enough ice to float in punch bowl to chill. Yield: approximately 50 to 75 servings.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Pick one loaf bread into pieces; arrange in cake size pan. Mix all other ingredients.
Spread mixture over bread.
Pick other loaf into pieces; put on top of mixture in pan.
Let raise 2 or 3 hours.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: spiced coffee
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients in blender for 15 seconds.
Stir. Then blend for 15 seconds more.
Store the mixture in a tightly covered container.

title: lazy pierogi
directions: Cook noodles; drain and set aside.
Core and cook cabbage (quartered).
Add lemon juice to water while cooking 25 minutes until done.
Drain and dice cabbage.
Brown hamburger; drain and set aside in bowl.
In same pan, place salt pork.
On low heat, cook until most of drippings are out.
Discard pork rind.
To drippings add 1 stick butter.
Saute onions and cabbage.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Blend in hamburger (if using) to pan mixture.

title: halfway house beans
directions: Cook green beans and drain.
Fry bacon and drain.
Chop onion and saute in fat.
Add tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer until soft, about 20 minutes.
Add beans and crumbled bacon; stir together.
Serves 8.

title: mock cordon bleu
directions: Lay beef slices on bottom of baking dish.
Wrap each piece of chicken with a slice of bacon.
Lay on top of beef slices.
Mix and blend well cream cheese, cream of chicken soup and sour cream. Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Excellent served with rice.

title: last minute chili
directions: Brown hamburger, then add mix, water and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil; let simmer for 15 minutes.
Spoon into bowls.
Top with sour cream, cheese and peppers.

title: caramel apple pie
directions: Preheat oven and baking sheet to 400°.
In a medium bowl, combine apples, sugar and flour; set aside.
In a double boiler, melt caramels with milk, stirring frequently.
Add apple mixture. Spoon mixture into pie crust and top with nuts.
Bake for 25 minutes; allow to cool 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped topping.

title: snowball snacks
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Stir butter, sugar, nuts, flour and vanilla together. Mix well. Roll batter into 1-inch balls with your hands. Place balls on the cookie sheet and bake for 10 minutes. After the cookies cool, roll them in additional confectioners sugar to make the snowballs.

title: monster cookies(yields 13 dozen)
directions: Mix in large bowl in order given.
Put out on cookie sheet with a teaspoon.
Flatten, then bake.
Do not overbake.
Bake at 350° for approximately 12 minutes.

title: sausage and cheese balls
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Mix by hand to blend.
Drop into balls on a cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 12 minutes.
Drain on paper towels and serve.

title: coffee cake
directions: Beat eggs until light. Add sugar, oil, flour, salt and baking powder. Spread half of the batter in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Spread a can of pie filling, any kind, apple is good, on batter, then add the rest of the batter.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes. Over the hot cake, drizzle 1/2 cup powdered sugar mixed with a little water. Good warm or cold.

title: easy salad(6 servings)
directions: Peel and slice oranges.
Discard seed.
Peel and slice cucumber.
Chop onion and green bell pepper.
Arrange lettuce on flat dish and put oranges and cucumber in alternating slices. Sprinkle with onion and green bell pepper.
Serve cold with olive oil, vinegar (wine) and salt.

title: pecan chocolate chip pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, flour, salt and bourbon or vanilla.
Add chocolate chips and pecans.
Stir well.
Pour into partially baked pie shell and bake for 30 minutes or until center is set (up to 60 minutes).
Serve with vanilla ice cream or frozen yogurt.
(It's better to cool pie well before serving and reheat in the microwave.)

title: raisin-carrot salad(serves 8)
directions: Rinse raisins in hot water; drain.
Cool and combine with remaining ingredients.
Chill and serve on crisp lettuce.

title: no bake oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute. Add last 3 ingredients and stir.
Continue cooking on low until thickens.
Drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Let cool.

title: blueberry salad gelatin mold
directions: You will need a 4-quart kettle or pot.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese.
Pour 1/2 mixture in well-greased hot skillet.
Iron skillet is best.
Sprinkle 1/2 cheese on top of mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, corn syrup and evaporated milk in heavy saucepan.
Bring to a boil over low heat, stirring constantly. Cook for 4 minutes or to 234° to 240° on candy thermometer (soft ball stage).
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter and vanilla; beat with spoon until thickened.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch buttered dish.
Let stand until set.
Cut into squares. Yields 24 squares.

title: cinnamon apple muffins
directions: Stir together flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and cinnamon. Combine egg, milk and oil.
Add all at once along with apples to dry ingredients.
Stir until dry ingredients are moist.
Do not overmix.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes at 375°.
While warm, dip the top in margarine and then into sugar.
Makes 12 muffins.

title: corn casserole
directions: Empty both cans of corn in casserole dish.
Sprinkle crackers over corn.
Melt margarine or butter.
Drizzle over crackers. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: lemonade cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour and soda.
Mix in lemonade that has been thawed.
Drop from teaspoon onto cookie sheet.
Brush top with lemonade and sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch cheesecake bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350° oven (325° for glass dish).
Melt morsel and margarine together; stir in graham cracker crumbs and nuts. Press half the mixture firmly onto the bottom of a greased 13 x 9 inch pan.
In large mixing bowl beat the cream cheese until fluffy; then add the Eagle Brand Milk, vanilla and the egg;
mix well.
Pour over crust in pan and top with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake for 25-30 minutes or until toothpick inserted near center comes out clean.
Cool to room temperature; then chill before cutting into bars.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: microwave puffy cheese omelet
directions: In largest mixer bowl beat
egg whites at highest speed until soft peaks form.
In
smaller
bowl
using same beaters, beat yolks, mayonnaise and
water.
Gently
pour
yolk mixture over beaten whites. Fold
together
carefully.
In
9-inch pie plate microwave butter at High 1
minute,
swirl to coat dish. Carefully pour
egg mixture
into
pie
plate.
Microwave
at Medium 6 to 8 minutes, rotating dish 1/2 turn after 3 minutes, until
set, but still glossy
on
top.
Sprinkle
cheese
over omelet.
Microwave 1/2 to 1 minute
on Medium, until cheese is slightly melted. Quickly run
spatula
or turner around sides and bottom of dish. Fold half
of omelet over the other half. Gently slide onto serving
plate.
Sprinkle
with
chives,
if desired.

title: indian tapioca pudding
directions: In the top of a double boiler, heat 3 cups milk. While the milk is heating, mix: cornmeal, quick tapioca, sugar, salt, cinnamon and ginger.
Pour the hot milk over this mixture in a saucepan and add molasses.
Bake in a greased casserole or in a pan set in another pan of water in a 350° oven, stirring every 15 minutes until done, about 2 hours.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: In a saucepan, dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add broccoli and cook until tender.
Do not drain.
In another large saucepan, melt the butter and cook the onion until tender.
Stir in flour and blend well.
Add milk.
Stir until thickened.
Add cheese. Stir until melted.
Add the broccoli and liquid.
Combine.
Heat, but do not boil.
Serves 3 or 4.

title: chicken chimichangas
directions: Combine chicken, green onions, cumin, oregano and salt in a large sauce pan.
Stir in 2/3 cup salsa or picante.
Cook over medium heat for 5 minutes, stirring often. Spoon about 2 tablespoons of chicken mixture just below the center of each tortilla; sprinkle evenly with half of the cheese.
Fold left and right sides of tortilla to partially enclose filling.
Fold up top and bottom edges of tortilla (making a square).
Place folded side down in a lightly greased baking dish, coated with Pam.
Repeat procedure with the remaining tortillas.
Bake at 475° for 13 minutes.
Heat remaining salsa in a small sauce pan; pour over tortillas and sprinkle evenly with the remaining cheese.
Top with sour cream if desired.

title: hot brats
directions: Brown brats in oil; drain.
Add beer to sausages.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add other items to pan and cook until thick. Serve warm with picks.

title: molded waldorf salad
directions: Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in small saucepan.
Cook and stir over low heat until gelatin dissolves, about 3 minutes. Remove from heat and stir in sugar, salt and juices until sugar dissolves.
Chill until thickened and very syrupy.
Fold in apples, celery and walnuts.
Turn into 1 quart mold and chill until firm.
Unmold on greens and serve with mayonnaise.

title: broccoli-cauliflower salad
directions: Combine broccoli and cauliflower.
Stir together the mayonnaise, yogurt, vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables and toss.
Chill 3 to 4 hours.
Salad will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: banana muffins
directions: In a bowl, mix together the butter, sugars, banana and egg. Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt; add to the first mixture alternately with the milk.
Place in greased or paper lined muffin tins and bake at 400° for 15-20 minutes.
Makes 8 or 9 muffins.

title: under-the-sea salad
directions: Dissolve jello in
hot
water
and add pear juice, salt and vinegar.
Put 1/2-inch
in
mold or reserve to use on top. Let remainder of jello slightly jell, then whip.
Cream cheese and ginger.
Add to
whipped jello.
Fold in fruit.
Fill mold or put in 9
x
13-inch
shallow
dish.
When
set, cover with reserved jello.

title: mushroom macaroni medley
directions: Melt butter in a pan; stir in flour, salt, pepper, Tabasco sauce, cheese and mushroom soup.
(Add a little water to soup; cook until slightly thickened.)
Mix together macaroni, dried beef and parsley.
Add the sauce and put in a buttered casserole or 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix well.
Shape into loaf or meat balls rolled in dry rice. Bake at 375° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Fry seasoned pork chops in iron skillet, using the 1 tablespoon of olive oil, until golden brown.
Cook rice separately.
Slice onion, bell pepper and tomato.
Place pork chops in iron skillet.
Place onion, bell pepper and tomato on top of pork chops.
Cover with rice.
Add gravy and cover.
Let simmer on low heat for 5 to 10 minutes.
Serve with salad.

title: muffin pan rolls
directions: Mix together.
Put in refrigerator until ready to use.
When ready to use, stir and spoon dough into muffin pans.
Let set for 15 minutes.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: easy microwaved pickled broccoli
directions: Eat and enjoy all the pickles, saving the jar and the remaining juice.
Wash and cut the broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Stuff the broccoli into the jar until full or the liquid covers the broccoli near the top.

title: steak fajitas
directions: Prepare beef according to taste.
Melt 1 tablespoon of butter in frying pan.
Add green pepper and onion.
Fry until onion is cooked.
Add prepared steak chopped into bite-sized pieces with remaining butter.
Cook until steak is done.
Add taco seasoning to meat.
Stir until blended.
Heat tortillas separately in microwave about 30 seconds.
Put ingredients on tortillas, about 3 tablespoons each, roll and serve.

title: dream whip cake
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Blend until moistened. Beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into 2 greased and floured 9-inch pans and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool cakes for 10 minutes in the pans.
Remove and finish cooling on racks. Frost or top with fruit, syrup or ice cream.

title: pork chops italian
directions: Remove bone from each pork chop.
Flatten to 1/4-inch thickness, using a meat mallet; dredge in flour.
Combine egg and water.
Dip each pork chop in egg mixture and dredge in bread crumbs.

title: tomato and onion salad
directions: In medium bowl, mix olive oil and red wine vinegar.
Adjust amounts to taste.
Add all seasonings, again to desired taste. Wash, dry and halve tomatoes, removing the seeds and soft insides. Cut thin slices of the halved tomatoes.
Add these slices and thinly sliced onion to mixture in bowl.
Mix thoroughly and frequently to marinate.
Serve at room temperature.

title: mocha almond torte
directions: Spread almonds on a baking dish.
Bake at 300° for several minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and cool.
Melt marshmallows in coffee over low heat.
Use a fairly large pot and stir often while marshmallows are melting.
When coffee mixture is smooth, remove from heat and cool.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Cream 2 tablespoons butter with the cream cheese, 1/4 cup sugar and cornstarch.
Add 1 egg, 2 tablespoons milk and 1/2 teaspoon vanilla; beat until smooth.
Grease and flour bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Place in bowl the flour, 2 cups sugar, salt, baking powder, soda, 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup milk.
Blend, then beat for 1 1/2 minutes at a low speed.
Add 1/3 cup milk, 2 eggs, Choco-bake and 1 teaspoon vanilla; beat 1 1/2 minutes.
Spread half of batter in pan.
Spoon cheese mixture over batter; spread to cover.
Top with remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar or chocolate frosting.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream butter and sugar, then mix in eggs and pumpkin.

title: normandy cake
directions: Cream butter and add egg yolks.
Cream again.
Add 1/2 of sugar.
Add alternately flour and milk.
Add melted chocolate and vanilla.
Beat egg whites and add remaining sugar to these.
Fold into cake mixture.
Last and most important, add baking powder by sifting it on the top of mixture, cutting and folding it in.
Bake in 3 layers in hot oven at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix pretzels and oleo together.
Press in dish.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: applesauce sugar-free cake
directions: Cook raisins and water until water is gone.
Beat applesauce, eggs and oil.
Add flour, cinnamon, nutmeg, soda, vanilla and sweetener.
Mix with raisins. Place in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: fri chik roast
directions: Save liquid from Fri Chik.
Mix with other liquids.
Pour over grated Fri Chiks and bread crumbs.
Saute onions and celery in margarine.
Mix all together.
Bake in bread loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stir-fry rice
directions: Prepare rice. Prepare vegetables. Heat oil in wok or frypan. Saute on medium-high heat the onions and green peppers, 1 to 2 minutes. Add celery and broccoli and cook 2 minutes. Add rice; stir. Add chicken or other meat and carrots. Season with garlic salt, Morton Nature's Season and soy sauce and stir. Turn heat off to serve. Add soy sauce to taste.

title: filling balls
directions: Saut celery and onion in margarine until soft and then add all other ingredients.
Mix well and form into balls.
Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 30 minutes or until browned.

title: homemade bread(for bread machine)
directions: Combine altogether.
This is made in a pound and half bread machine.
You can use on dough and make into rolls and bake in the oven at 350 degrees until golden brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Slice bananas, reserving two, and empty cookies; set aside.
Combine 1/2 cup of sugar, flour and dash of salt in double boiler over boiling water.
Pour in egg yolks and both milks, stirring constantly until it thickens.
Reduce heat and cook for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add vanilla extract, blending well.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together and dip prepared raw vegetables. Note!
Good on chips, too.

title: homemade stuffing
directions: Mix all ingredients. Spread in 9 x 13 pan. Squeeze butter on top. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: frankfurter pie
directions: Reserve 4 frankfurters.
Cut remaining into 1-inch pieces. Heat oil in medium saucepan.
Add onion and green pepper and cook until soft.
Add cut frankfurters; saute until frankfurters begin to brown.
Remove from heat.
Stir in sauerkraut, mustard, pimento and Worcestershire sauce.
Cut each slice of bread in half from corner to corner; flatten with rolling pin.
Line pie plate with bread.
Top with sauerkraut mix.
Cut remaining franks and top the sauerkraut mixture.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes.

title: all purpose bread recipe
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water with the sugar.
Add eggs, oil, salt and enough flour to make dough.
Knead until smooth.
Cover and let rise once.
Shape into rolls, buns or 4 (8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch) loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Good also for Caramel Rolls.

title: o honey bars
directions: Mix together Special K and peanut butter.
In saucepan, mix Karo and sugar; bring to boil and pour over other mixture.
Pour in buttered 9 x 13-inch or little longer pan.
Run cold water over hands and pat down.
Melt chocolate chips and spread on top. Cool, cut and enjoy.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Preferably, chill about 4 hours before serving to allow time for flavors to meld.
Serve with crackers.

title: molasses cookies
directions: Combine the sugar, ginger, nutmeg, cinnamon, salt and baking soda. Mix well. Add the melted margarine, evaporated milk and molasses. Add the extracts. The dough should be still enough to handle without sticking to the fingers. Knead the dough for a smoother texture. Add up to 1/2 cup additional flour if necessary to prevent sticking. When dough is smooth, roll about 1/4 inch thick
on floured board and cut into cookies. Bake in preheated 375° oven for 10 to 12 minutes. Cookies are done if they spring back when touched.

title: chili
directions: Brown hamburger in skillet. Drain off the grease and add remaining ingredients. Cook about 45 minutes until done.

title: yulekage(norwegian christmas bread)
directions: Put sugar, salt, butter and milk powder into a large bowl. Bring potato water to a boil and pour over first 4 ingredients. Let cool to lukewarm.
(Potato water is water potatoes have been boiled in.
If you don't have potato water, you can use plain water and add 2 tablespoons instant potato flakes to the first 4 ingredients.
Potato water helps make a moist loaf that doesn't become stale quickly.)
Add eggs and yeast mixture (yeast, water and 2 teaspoons sugar) to bowl.
Beat in about 4 cups of flour plus the cardamon.
Gradually beat in more flour until the dough is stiff enough to handle on the bread board.

title: nacho chips - hot
directions: Cook and drain hamburger; add taco mix according to directions.
Add soups.

title: oven-barbecued chicken
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; stir well.
Dredge chicken in flour mixture.
Pour butter into a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Arrange chicken in pan, skin side down.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: salmon patties ole
directions: Combine salmon, potatoes, chilies, onion and egg.
Form into patties.
Pan-fry in butter over medium heat until golden brown, turning when needed.

title: frozen cucumbers
directions: Mix and soak first 3 ingredients for 2 hours.
Drain and add other ingredients.
Pack in jars or containers and freeze.
When ready to serve, thaw about 1 hour.

title: persimmon pudding(uncooked)
directions: Mix all together.
Pack in pan and chill overnight.
Serve with whipped cream.

title: brown sugar pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a 10-inch Bundt pan or tube pan.
In a small bowl, combine flour and baking powder; set aside.
In a large bowl, with electric mixer at high speed, cream butter and brown sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
At low speed, alternately add flour mixture and 1 cup milk until well-blended.
Pour batter into prepared pan. Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours or until cake tester inserted in center comes out clean.
Remove pan to wire rack; cool 15 minutes. Remove cake from pan; cool completely.

title: sweet potatoes and apples
directions: Place sweet potatoes in baking dish. Scatter apples over. In bowl, mix brown sugar, cornstarch and nutmeg; stir in 1 cup apple juice (cold). Melt oleo in saucepan with 1 cup apple juice and heat. Stir in sugar mixture; boil, stirring until thickened. Pour over sweet potatoes and apples, baking at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes. Serves 8 to 10. Can freeze. Can do ahead.

title: prune cake
directions: Mix the first 5 ingredients together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and bake in a greased and floured tube pan. Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Start in a 200° oven for 45 minutes.
Increase oven to 300° the rest of time.

title: old fashioned tea cake
directions: Put all ingredients into tray of sifted flour. Work together until dough will handle.
Roll out on board and cut with cookie cutter at 375°.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Place chicken breasts in casserole.
Combine remaining ingredients and pour over chicken.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Bake 1 1/2 hours, covered.
Remove foil and bake 15 more minutes, letting chicken brown.

title: miniature cheesecakes
directions: Combine crumbs and butter; stir well.
Line 1 3/4-inch muffin pans with miniature paper liners.
Spoon 1 teaspoon mixture into each liner; gently press into bottom.
Place cream cheese in a small bowl; beat at low speed of electric mixer until fluffy. Gradually add sugar, beating until fluffy.
Add egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Spoon evenly into liners.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: guaranteed dinner rolls
directions: Soften yeast in warm water with 1 teaspoon sugar.
Stir in salt and 1/3 cup sugar; mix well.
Stir in yeast mixture; add well beaten egg to mixture.
Mix; add 3 cups of flour, stirring mixture until it is smooth elastic.
Add corn oil; mix.
Add remaining 3 cups flour; mix well.
Cover with wax paper; let rise until dough has doubled.
Knead dough in remaining flour; roll dough to 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick.
Cut to desired shapes; place in greased pan. Cover; let rise until double in size.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in preheated oven at 400°.
Rub butter on top when rolls are light brown.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: cheese cake
directions: Beat egg white until stiff and set aside.
Mix cream cheese, 1 cup sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and milk together and beat well. Place 1 can of crescent rolls in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan. Press to cover the bottom.
Spread cream cheese mixture over rolls. Press the other can of rolls together on wax paper and place on top.
Take egg whites and spread over the rolls.
Sprinkle another 1/4 cup sugar over top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put all ingredients in bowl and stir to mix.

title: cheesecake
directions: Place drained pineapple in blender with half of juice.
Add gelatin and hot water.
Blend 2 minutes.
Add dry milk and remainder of juice, sweetener, vanilla, butter flavoring and lemon juice.
Blend
3 minutes.
Pour in 10-inch pan.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and allow to set 1 hour, at least.
Cut into 8 pieces.

title: fudge
directions: Melt chocolate chips.
Add sweetened milk.
Add marshmallows, then vanilla.
Put in buttered pan.

title: fish chowder
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Place in boiling water and cook for 5 minutes to soften.
Drain.
Put 2 tablespoons oleo in bottom of 6 quart kettle along with fish, 4 tablespoons water and salt pork. Simmer on low until fish is light and flaky and fully cooked.
Add potatoes, evaporated milk and whole milk, and remaining oleo. Simmer, uncovered, stirring occasionally to avoid sticking until oleo is melted and milk is warm.
Do not boil.

title: nan pie
directions: Mix together lemonade and milk well; fold Cool Whip into lemonade and milk.
Place in graham cracker crust.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Fry sausage.
Drain.
Fry potatoes in oil.
Drain.
Add bell pepper to potatoes.
Grate cheese.
Press rolls on pizza pan to form crust.
Add potatoes, sausage, cheese and pour beaten eggs over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: ham and cheese finger sandwiches
directions: Cream butter, onion, mustard and poppy seed.
With electric knife, slice package of ready to serve dinner rolls in half (separating top from bottom).
Spread mixture on both top and bottom of bread.
Lay slices of ham covering bread.
Sprinkle sandwiches with cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve hot.

title: sour cream chicken casserole
directions: Mix soup and sour cream with chicken.
Layer bottom of buttered casserole dish with crackers.
Spoon mixture over crackers.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Sprinkle more crackers over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: dip for fruit
directions: Combine egg and sugar and mix well.
Add juices and heat until thickened, then add the orange and lemon peel.
Cool mixture and then add the mayonnaise.

title: banana blueberry bran muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Line with paper baking cups or grease (not oil) 12 muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine rolled oats and orange juice; stir well.
Add slightly beaten egg and oil. (Lightly spoon flour into measuring cup; level off.)

title: fried potatoes and onions
directions: Mix all ingredients together except oil.
Pour oil into large skillet and heat on medium heat till hot.
Place all mixture into pan and fry, stirring occasionally to keep from sticking, until potatoes and onions are golden brown and tender.
Drain onto paper towels, and enjoy.

title: bridal punch (lime green)
directions: Mix lemon juice, lime juice, Sprite and pineapple juice.
When ready to serve, add sherbet and Fresca.
Serves 30.

title: linda's favorite hot little wiener hors d'oeuvres
directions: Cut hot dogs in half. Cut bacon strips in half. Wrap bacon around hot dog.
Carefully place in crock-pot so that the bacon stays on the hot dog.
Sprinkle brown sugar over and cook on high for 1 hour.
Serve hot. Easy to make and fun to eat.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown beef.
Add Ragu.
Cook spaghetti 4 minutes.
In a large dish put a layer of beef, layer of spaghetti, layer of cheese, layer of beef, layer of spaghetti soup and rest of cheese.
Bake 35 minutes at 300°.

title: mrs. wilson chicken casserole
directions: Put fat from chicken, flour and mushroom pieces together.
Add enough milk to make about 3 cups.
Mix altogether and put in a pan (9 x 13-inches); cover with cheese (cut up).
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: succotash
directions: In a small saucepan, combine all ingredients and heat thoroughly.

title: shrimp pate
directions: Mash shrimp; add remaining ingredients.
Serve on garlic Melba rounds.

title: chicago deep-dish pizza
directions: On lightly floured surface, allow dough to stand, covered, at room temperature for 1 hour or until doubled in volume.
Remove sausage from casing.
Brown meat; drain.
Add onions and cook until tender.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato paste and oregano; simmer 15 minutes.
Roll out dough to 15 x 11-inch rectangle; press onto bottom and 1-inch up sides of greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cover with half of Mozzarella cheese and meat sauce.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes.
Let stand 15 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: chicken dijon casserole
directions: Bake chicken breasts or other chicken pieces, basted with 1 stick butter until done.
Saute mushrooms and onion in butter until tender.
Add drippings from chicken, cream of chicken soup, sour cream, Dijon mustard, salt and pepper to taste.
Cook one package wide egg noodles and add 1 package frozen peas, which have been cooked according to package directions.
Place in serving dish.
Top with chicken and cover with sauce.
Reheat, if necessary.

title: broccoli salad
directions: In a bowl, combine mayonnaise, relish, sugar, salt and pepper. Add celery and onion; mix well.
Add broccoli and toss gently. Chill until serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix well.
Use for spinach salad or red lettuce.

title: puppy chow
directions: Microwave chocolate, peanut butter and butter 1 to 1 1/2 minutes, stirring after 1 minute.
Add vanilla and pour over Chex and mix gently.
Place sugar in a large Ziploc bag. Add coated Chex and shake to coat.
Spread on wax paper to cool.
Return to Ziploc bag.
(I add more powdered sugar at this time.)

title: green bean, corn and tomato salad
directions: Cook beans in salted water for 2 minutes.
Add corn kernels; cook 2 minutes and drain well.
Whisk vinegar, oil and sugar in bowl.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add beans, corn, tomatoes, onion and parsley; toss to coat.
Season again with salt and pepper.
Chill.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in bowl; add eggs, margarine, buttermilk and flavorings.
Mix well.
Turn into pastry shell. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes longer.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: carrot cake
directions: Reserve
juice	from pineapple to put between layers or on sheet cake pan.

title: chocolate vanilla fluff
directions: Pat all in bottom of 12 x 8 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: caramel pie
directions: Place 1/2 cup sugar in iron skillet; cook until it turns a dark brown syrup.
Remove from heat and add boiling water.
Cream eggs, sugar, flour, milk, butter and syrup.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until thick.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Top with Meringue.

title: quick rolls
directions: Preheat oven to ???.
Combine all ingredients.
Stir until moistened.
Drop by teaspoons into greased muffin tins.
Cook for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 20 rolls.

title: basic white or cream sauce
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour in the top of a double boiler and let simmer for a few minutes to remove the raw flour taste. Stir milk in gradually, using a spoon or whisk.
Continue stirring until mixture thickens and comes to a boil.
Add salt and allow sauce to cook over hot water about 5 minutes.
For cream sauce, add cream instead of milk.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Combine dry ingredients in a large bowl.
Make a well in the center.
In a separate small bowl, mix remaining 5 ingredients together.
Pour fruit mixture into well and gently stir by hand.
Coat 2 nonstick
9 x 5-inch bread pans with cooking spray and pour mixture into pans.
Bake for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool before slicing.

title: deviled crab
directions: Crumble saltines in cream. Add butter and cook until thick. Cool. Add beaten egg and fold in crabmeat.
Season with red pepper, salt and pepper.
Place in crab shells and brush with melted butter. Broil until brown, about 15 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: jay's soft sugar cookies
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder, salt and milk.
Stir well.
Chill at least 1 hour. Roll in balls (1 1/2 to 2-inches); flatten and round out with hands on ungreased cookie sheet.
Don't make them too thin.
Bake in preheated oven, 350°, for 10 to 12 minutes.
Do not overbake.

title: corn meal pancakes
directions: Mix well in a medium bowl with a wire whisk.
Fry in a small amount of oil in a hot frying pan.
Makes 6 pancakes.

title: posie cream frosting
directions: Operate mixer at low speed, mix shortening, salt, 1 c. sugar, butter and vanilla until smooth. Gradually beat in the rest of the sugar, and beat until smooth spreading consistency.

title: cupcake cones
directions: Prepare mix as package directs.
Fill cones with 2 tablespoons mixture, baking 6 cones at a time.
Microwave 1 to 1 1/4 minutes or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Frost with whipped cream or frosting.
Makes 24 to 30 cones.

title: black bottom pie
directions: Bake pie shell. Stir together 1/2 cup sugar, cornstarch and salt in saucepan. Blend milk and egg yolk.
Stir into sugar mixture. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, just until mixture boils. Reserve 1 cup of custard mixture.
Set aside.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Mix the soup, water, onion, salt and pepper in a bowl.
Pour over potatoes which are placed in a buttered casserole.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350° to 375°.
Let sit for a few minutes prior to serving.

title: easy low-fat pineapple casserole
directions: Toss bread cubes and pineapple in bowl.
Spoon in greased 2-quart baking dish.
Beat eggs with sugar; pour over pineapple mixture.
Dot with butter.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Yields 8 servings.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Mix dressing, cumin and pepper; stir in chicken. Spoon 1/3 cup of chicken mixture onto tortilla; roll up. Place seam side down in 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Pour salsa over filled tortillas. Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes. Serve over hot cooked rice with chopped red peppers. Makes 4 servings.

title: greek oven fries
directions: Soak garlic in olive oil for at least 1 hour.
Scrub potatoes; cut lengthwise into 8 wedges each.
Place wedges in a bowl and cover with very cold water.
Allow to stand for 30 minutes.
Drain and pat dry with paper towels.
Remove garlic from oil.
Toss wedges in oil until coated.
Coat baking sheet with cooking spray. Place potatoes, skin side down, on baking sheet.
Sprinkle potatoes with oregano, salt and pepper.
Bake at 400° for 50 minutes.
Serve with malt vinegar.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix the corns and 1/2 box muffin mix.
Pour in a greased casserole dish.
Spread sour cream over the corn and muffin mixture, then sprinkle cheese on, then the rest of muffin mix.
Dot with oleo.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (uncovered).

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix thoroughly in the order listed and chill.
Put into graham cracker crust.
Makes 2 pies.

title: chocolate cherry bars
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk and boil 1 minute.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate chips.
When melted, pour over partially cooled bars.

title: baked garlic sausages with mushrooms
directions: Split sausages.
Arrange in a greased, shallow baking dish, just large enough to hold them in a single layer.
Saute mushrooms and onions in butter over medium heat until lightly browned. Smoothly mix in mustard and cream.
Bring to boiling.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until liquid is reduced and slightly thickened.

title: cassoulet
directions: Cook and stir ground beef, celery, onion, pepper and garlic until veggies are tender.
Pour off excess fat.
Stir in salt and beans with liquid.
Stir in tomato paste.
Simmer 10 minutes.

title: lillian's grandmother's meatballs
directions: Mix all of above together.
Keep hands wet and shape meat into dome-like shape (not too large and not too round).
If meat feels too dense, add a little more milk.
If too soft, add a little more bread crumbs.
Place in a very hot frying pan (with whatever oil you like, preferably olive oil) and fry at low flame until golden brown on the outside.
Do not cook completely.
Add meatballs to gravy the last hour of cooking; continue to simmer.
Skim any fat from frying pan.
