Add a little water or red wine, 2 tablespoons tomato paste and mix with meat particles left in pan.
Add dash of sugar; simmer, covered, for a few minutes to take the tartness out.
Add this to the gravy.

title: banana cake(large)
directions: Mix thoroughly the eggs, sugar and butter.
Add bananas; mix well.
Add vanilla and cake flour.
Mixture must be quite thick, so add more flour, if not thick enough.
Add baking powder with flour.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1/2 can of onions.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Stir.
Top with remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.

title: crab imperial
directions: Combine and mix.
Heap in shells or small bowls.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place cookies on baking sheet and bake at 300° until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli. Arrange in a 1 1/2-quart casserole. Combine soup, butter, lemon juice and cheese. Spoon over broccoli.
Top with crackers, almonds and pimento. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: roast moose
directions: Place roast in roaster with a small amount of fat.
Add seasonings; cover.
Roast at 250° for 45 minutes per pound, basting often.
Pour wine over roast during last 30 minutes.
Use meat thermometer for desired results.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add 1/2 cup taco sauce; stir and heat.
Crush bag of Doritos; set aside.
Shred lettuce. Toss with diced tomatoes, chopped olives and minced onions.
Add Doritos; toss.
Add 1 to 2 cups shredded Cheddar cheese.
Stir in ground beef mixture.
Stir in Thousand Island dressing.

title: weight watcher's pumpkin muffins
directions: Mix the dry ingredients.
Beat eggs.
Add raisins, pumpkin and carrots to eggs.
Spray muffin pan with Pam.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Counts as 1 bread, 1 fruit, 1 protein, 1 milk and 1 vegetable.)

title: apple cheesecake
directions: Cream ingredients together and spread "dough" into bottom of spring-form pan.
Bring dough 1/2-inch up the sides.
Place in freezer while making filling.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour this over batter and bake 45 minutes in 375° oven.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Put into greased baking dish. Add cheese and butter.
Sprinkle generously with crushed Ritz crackers.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: mexican frito salad
directions: Prepare lettuce for salad.
Chill beans and add to lettuce, tomatoes, onions and cheese.
Pour 3/4 bottle of dressing over all and toss lightly.
Just before serving, add crushed Fritos and toss.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Brown beef in hot oil.
Add onion, mushrooms, green pepper (optional), seasonings and tomato juice.
Cover.
When steaming, reduce heat and simmer without lid for 45 minutes.

title: apple or cherry dump cake
directions: Layer pie filling, then pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle cake mix on top.
Melt margarine and drizzle on top.
Bake approximately 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: gazpacho
directions: Remove crust from bread and dip slices in wine vinegar. Combine all ingredients in a blender.
Add enough water to fill blender and liquefy.
(If there is not enough room in the blender, add 1 to 2 cups of water and blend in 2 batches.)
Soup should not be watery.
Chill well before serving.

title: hot dogs in sauce
directions: Place hot dogs in a baking dish.
Mix all other ingredients together.
Pour over hot dogs.
Bake in covered dish for 1 hour at 350 degrees.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Layer rice in a shallow pan.
Sprinkle dry onion soup mix over rice.
Put a layer of raw chicken over dry soup.
Pour 1 can of creamed soup mixed with water over all.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: philadelphia cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream together first 3 ingredients.
Add the eggs, beating well after each.
Add the flour.
Then add the salt and vanilla. Bake 1 hour at 325°.
This cake may be baked in small loaf pans to be given as gifts.

title: onion soup bistro
directions: *Granulated beef and chicken bouillon may be substituted.

title: glazed sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Arrange sweet potatoes in 1 1/2-quart shallow baking dish.
Spoon preserves over sweet potatoes.
Top with nuts, marshmallows and margarine.
Bake 25 minutes or microwave on High 6 to 7 minutes.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: orange freeze
directions: Put the sherbet, juice, and milk in a blender and blend for 15 seconds or just until the sherbet is smooth.
You may have to stop the blender and stir the sherbet up a bit to help it combine. Pour the orange freeze into a tall, chilled glass.
Place a sprig of fresh spearmint in the top and serve immediately.

title: lemon chess pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and add to unbaked pie crust. Cook in 450° oven for about 15 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and cook 20 minutes.

title: busy day fruit cobbler
directions: Place fruit in greased 8 x 8-inch pan.
(If fruit is very juicy, mix 1 tablespoon cornstarch with each cup of juice.)
Cream shortening and sugar.
Mix in egg.
Add flour and milk alternately; mix until smooth after each addition.
Pour over fruit in pan (9 x 13-inch).
Bake in 375° oven for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: chicken-sour cream casserole
directions: Combine butter and cracker crumbs; blend well.
Spoon half the crumbs into a shallow, 2-quart casserole; cover with chicken. Combine sour cream, soup, broth, salt and pepper; blend well. Pour over chicken and top with the remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
(Ritz crackers give an even more buttery flavor.)
Yields 6 servings.

title: rainbow salad
directions: First Layer:
Add juice of pineapple to lime Jell-O; cool.
Add pineapple.
When almost congealed, add second layer with spoon.

title: cheese souffle
directions: Mix butter (or margarine) with the mustard.
Spread on each slice of bread.
Cut bread into cubes.
Put a layer of bread in bottom of dish, then some of the cheese cubes.
Then add rest of the bread and rest of the cheese.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and paprika together.
Pour over bread and cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350° to 375° until brown on top and sides.

title: beef bourguignon
directions: Brown meat fast in hot fat in heavy skillet.
Pour sherry over and transfer to medium casserole.
Salt lightly.
In remaining fat, saute onions and mushrooms lightly; stir in tomato paste, meat glaze and flour.
Add slowly, consomme and 1/4 cup wine.
Stir until boils.
Season to taste and pour over beef in casserole.
Add bouquet garni.
Cover and cook in slow oven (250°) about 3 hours until meat is tender and cuts with a fork.
Add remaining wine at intervals.
Serves 6.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Brown hamburger and drain grease. Combine remaining ingredients in pan with meat and simmer (no water).

title: scalloped potatoes with ham
directions: Combine soup, milk, onion, salt and pepper. Arrange alternate layers of potatoes, ham and soup mixture in 1 1/2-quart casserole. Bake, covered, in a 325° oven for 1 hour, then uncovered for 25 to 30 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese. Bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 4 servings.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Dissolve soda into water that you rinsed the tomato soup can with and mix with other ingredients.
Pour batter into a 9 x 13 x 2-inch square cake pan and bake in a 350° oven for about 35 minutes.
Frost with a cream cheese icing or white icing of your choice.
Sprinkle with additional chopped nuts, if desired.
This cake is very good without icing.

title: lasagna
directions: Saute ground beef, onion, bell pepper and garlic until meat is brown.
Add tomato paste, soup and hot sauce.
Simmer 30 minutes. Cook noodles as directed.
In greased baking dish, layer noodles, meat and cheese; repeat until mixture is gone, finishing with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 30 minutes or until cheese is bubbly.

title: molasses drop cookies
directions: Grease baking sheets.
Start oven 10 minutes before baking, set to moderately hot at 400°.
Wash raisins and plump, then cool. Chop nuts. Sift flour, measure and resift 4 times with the next 5 ingredients.
Press brown sugar through a coarse sieve to remove lumps.
In a 3-quart mixing bowl, cream butter and shortening with wooden spoon until smooth.
Add sugar and cream well.
Scrape spoon.
Remove.
Beat in egg with rotary beater until fluffy. Then beat molasses until satiny.
Remove beater and use spoon. Stir in flour mixture and milk alternately in 2 or 3 portions beginning and ending with flour and mixing until smooth after each portion.
Stir in raisins and nuts until well distributed.
Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls onto prepared sheet.
Bake about 10 minutes or until delicately browned.
Remove at once from sheet to cake rack.
When cool, store in box or jar with tight fitting lid with sheet of wax paper between each layer.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: sweet-sour pork
directions: Brown pork; add 1/3 cup water.
Cover and simmer until tender, about 1 hour.
Drain pineapple, reserving syrup.
Combine sugars and cornstarch.
Add pineapple, syrup, soy sauce and salt.
Add to pork; stir until thick.
Add pineapple, green pepper and onion. Cook 2 minutes.
Serve over hot rice or fried noodles and extra soy sauce.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; pour into 9 x 13-inch pan and freeze overnight.

title: lentil skillet supper
directions: Heat oil in large skillet over medium-high heat.
Add carrot, lentil and onion; cook, stirring constantly, for 3 to 4 minutes. Add broth and rice; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat to low.
Cover and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes, until liquid is absorbed.
Fluff with fork.
Remove from heat and sprinkle with cheese.
Cover; let stand 1 to 2 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Makes four 1-cup servings.

title: sweet-sour cabbage(surkal)
directions: Shred cabbage very fine.
Add other ingredients.
Cover with water and simmer for 1 to 2 hours.
Good served with roast pork.

title: french onion soup
directions: Heat butter in large skillet.
Add onions; saute, stirring, until golden, about 8 minutes.
Combine onions, bouillon, bay leaf, garlic and thyme.
Bring to boil; simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Mix asparagus, peas, mushroom soup and mayonnaise and pour into a casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and bake at 300° to 350° until bubbling (approximately 30 minutes).

title: shrimp creole
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients in frying pan with enough cooking oil to cover.
Simmer over low fire until clear.
Combine rest of ingredients; start to simmer on low heat with lid on.
After first mixture is completed, add to mixture but drain part of oil. Simmer for approximately 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: fluffy peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl, beat cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in milk and peanut butter until smooth.
Stir in lemon and vanilla.
Fold in whipped topping.
Turn into crust.
Drizzle chocolate syrup over top of pie and gently swirl with spoon.
Chill 4 hours or until set.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Add cooked onion to soup; add carrots and cheese.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with herb stuffing mix combined with 1/2 cup melted butter.
Spread on top.
Serves 6.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Mix all the ingredients, except nuts, in a saucepan and bring to a boil for 3 to 5 minutes or until the mixture forms a soft ball in cold water.
Take off of stove and stir in the pecan halves.
Keep stirring until all the syrup sticks to the nuts. Pour the nuts out onto a brown paper bag, separate, and let them cool.

title: california fresh fruit dip
directions: In a small bowl combine all ingredients.
Serve with fresh fruit.
Cover and refrigerate leftovers.
This is a nice dip for diabetics who want to jazz up their fresh fruit.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix ingredients together, except apples, for a crumb mixture. Pour over a 9 x 13-inch pan of sliced apples.
Bake in 375° oven for 35 minutes or until apples are done.

title: orange slice cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Cut orange slice candy into small pieces. Roll candy, dates and pecans in flour before mixing into cake.
Add this mixture to sugar, margarine and egg mixture.
Add flour.
Bake in tube pan for 2 hours and 45 minutes at 250°.

title: jello popcorn balls
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add marshmallows and stir until melted.
Add jello and pour over popped corn.
Butter hands and form popcorn into balls.
Be sure to let popcorn mixture cool slightly or you will burn your hands!

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion together until tender. Drain. Add sour cream, margarine, salt, nutmeg, black pepper, red pepper and slightly beaten egg.
Pour half of the squash into casserole dish. Cover with half of the potato chips and cheese. Add remaining squash, potato chips and cheese.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika. Cook in medium oven for 30 minutes.

title: aunt sally's eggs and tomatoes
directions: Cook onions in oleo until soft in a heavy iron skillet.
Pour tomatoes in skillet with onions; season to taste with salt and sugar.
Cook until not so watery.
Break eggs, one at a time, around in tomatoes.
Cover and cook until done.
Sprinkle with black pepper, if desired.

title: zucchini relish(given to me by a camper friend.)
directions: Mix zucchini and onions; add salt. Mix well. Wash and drain. In a large pan, add remaining ingredients. Mix well.
Simmer 5 to 10 minutes. Can in sterile jars. Process 5 minutes in boiling water. This insures sealing.

title: homemade vegetable soup
directions: Lightly brown ground beef in a small amount of oil; drain off excess fat.
Combine all ingredients in large kettle.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.

title: baked, mashed potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes, drain, and whip with margarine, salt, sour cream, and cream cheese (a small amount of milk may be added if desired).
Pour mashed potatoes in casserole dish.
Top with cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Bake at 350 degrees until cheese is melted and potatoes begin to bubble around the edges.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Wash and peel potatoes.
Grate potatoes.
Add beaten egg, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Add flour and onion and mix again.
Drop heaping tablespoonfuls of mixture onto hot griddle or frying pan, greased with oil or shortening.
Makes approximately 12 pancakes. Serve with sour cream or applesauce.

title: simple chicken italiano
directions: In a large skillet, combine chicken and about 1/3 of the Italian dressing.
Saute until chicken starts to brown.
Add veggies and remaining dressing.
Cover and simmer 7 to 9 minutes until veggies are crisp-tender, stirring frequently.
Serve over pasta; sprinkle with cheese.
Makes 5 servings.

title: sausage and egg casserole
directions: Break bread into pieces in bottom of greased pan. Brown sausage and drain.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over bread.

title: green pepper corn bread
directions: Combine eggs, buttermilk and oil; mix well.
Stir into corn meal until moist.
Add remaining ingredients and stir.
Pour into greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Dice these ingredients up together.

title: cheese ball
directions: Roll in a big round ball, let set in refrigerator and then roll in chopped walnuts.

title: rice pudding
directions: Rinse rice in warm water.
Cook rice in milk until thick.
Add salt, sugar and extracts.
Stir in small amount of hot mixture into beaten egg yolks, then add to rest of hot mixture.
Cook for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Mix
well
cream
cheese,
butter
and oleo.
Add eggs; beat. Add sugar, cake flour and vanilla.	Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°. Start in cold oven.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and flour with just enough hot water to make a thick batter.
Put the oil in an iron pan and heat hot.
Then pour off oil into batter.
Mix and pour in pan.
Squirt margarine on top.
Bake at 450° for approximately 25 minutes until nice and brown.

title: electric lemonade
directions: You will need a 1 gallon jar (glass).

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spray dish with Pam, 9 x 12-inch.
Place bread as a liner in bottom of pan.
Sprinkle with cheese and cooked sausage.
Mix together eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over sausage and cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, until eggs are set.

title: catherine darsey's bean sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients in order given.
Sauce can be served on green beans, broccoli, asparagus or other cooked vegetables. Leftover sauce should be refrigerated.

title: lemon-jello pound cake
directions: Mix together cake mix, milk, oil and eggs.
(Beat in one egg at a time.)
Pour mix into angel food cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cake cool 10 minutes.
Loosen edges of cake with knife.
Turn cake out of pan and onto plate.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Using an 8-quart pressure kettle, cook hen in salt, pepper and water on 10 pounds pressure for 50 minutes.
Cook chicken breasts, salt, pepper and water on 10 pounds pressure for 15 minutes. Remove chicken.
Add margarine to broth; set aside.

title: creamy tomato soup
directions: Melt butter in a medium saucepan over medium-low heat.
Add onion and garlic, and cook, stirring, until translucent, about 6 minutes.
Add tomatoes, stock and oregano and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer gently until thickened, about 45 minutes. Remove oregano sprigs.
Slowly add half and half, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper.
Garnish with oregano, if desired. Serve hot.

title: lime nut jello salad
directions: Mix jello and chill until slightly thickened.
Beat Dream Whip and cream cheese.
Add all ingredients to jello.
Refrigerate until jelled.
You can put in 9 x 13-inch pan and cut in squares. You can put it in a mold and you will still have some leftover. It makes a good portion.

title: eight layer salad
directions: Mix the first seven ingredients in layers.
Spread salad dressing on top 3/4 inch thick.
Sprinkle with sugar, salt and white pepper to taste.
Cover with grated Cheddar cheese 3/4 inch thick and top with crisp fried bacon (chopped).
Refrigerate 1 to 2 hours before serving.

title: russian rock cookies
directions: Mix sugar and butter, then add eggs and mix well.
Add nuts, dates and raisins that were floured well. Add cinnamon, soda, flour and vanilla. Drop by teaspoonfuls on a well-greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Stir together sugar and cornstarch.
Gradually stir in water until smooth. Stir in egg yolks.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Boil 1 minute.
Remove and stir in lemon juice and margarine; let cool and turn into pie shell.
Beat egg whites at high speed until foamy; gradually add 1/3 cup sugar and beat until stiff.
Lightly brown meringue at 350°.

title: red beans and rice
directions: Sort and wash beans; cover with water 2-inches over beans and soak overnight.
Add salt pork to beans; cover and simmer for 45 minutes.
Stir in next 10 ingredients and cook for 1 hour.
Brown sausage; drain and add to beans.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; beat well.
Put in a greased and floured cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Delicious!

title: morning glory muffins
directions: In large bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Stir in carrots, raisins and apples.
In separate bowl, beat eggs, oil and vanilla and stir into flour mixture.
Spoon into well-greased muffin cups (or paper-lined), filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes. Makes approximately 18 large muffins.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients (except potato chips) together and pour into large casserole.
Top with chips and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: marinated broccoli
directions: Mix the oil with the vinegar, water, lemon juice, garlic and seasonings.
In a large salad bowl with a tight-fitting lid, toss the mixture with the broccoli.
Let marinate all day or overnight, tossing the mixture several times before eating.

title: aunt wilma's coca-cola salad
directions: Drain fruit, retaining juice.
Heat juice and add Jell-O to dissolve.
Add cola and congeal.
Mix cream cheese with a small amount of mayonnaise or cream to thin slightly.
After Jell-O has partially congealed, add nuts, cream cheese and fruit.
Return to refrigerator to finish congealing.

title: granny's potato soup
directions: Dice potatoes small, rinse, put in saucepan, cover with water and cook over medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Add salt and pepper to taste and margarine.
Let simmer 3 to 4 minutes.
Add canned milk.
Bring to boil for 3 to 4 minutes.
Remove from heat and serve.

title: parmesan onion canapes
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Spread on lightly toasted bread. Place on baking sheets and broil 4 inches from heat source for 2 to 3 minutes or until golden and bubbly.
Very good!

title: fruit salad
directions: Bring to boil the water and sugar.
Cool and pour over the mixed fruits.
Chill.
You can also freeze this.

title: chicken lasagna rolls
directions: Preheat oven to 375°F. Spray a medium baking dish with vegetable cooking spray. Cook noodles according to package directions, but do not add salt. Drain and lay out flat on waxed paper. Meanwhile, prepare sauce. In a small saucepan, over medium-low heat, combine cream cheese, milk and Parmesan cheese, stirring until smooth. Set aside. Spray a large nonstick skillet with vegetable cooking spray. Heat skillet over medium heat. Add mushrooms and green onions. Cook, stirring, until tender, about 5 minutes. In a blender or food processor fitted with the metal blade, combine mushroom mixture, ricotta, chicken and parsley. Process until smooth. Spoon mushroom mixture down center of each noodle and roll up tightly. If you want, you can drizzle a small amount of the sauce down center of each noodle. Place rolls, filling sides up, in prepared dish. Spoon sauce on top. Cover with foil. Bake rolls until heated through, about 25 minutes. Serve immediately.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Sift cake mix and jello into bowl.
Add oil, eggs and warm water and beat well.
Add strawberries and mix well.
Pour into 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: quick biscuits
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing as for a cake.
Fill muffin pans about half full, leveling with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes, then increase to 450° to brown.
Makes 8 biscuits.

title: ruby plylers apple jack pastry
directions: Roll out dough, cut biscuit size, seal edges with water. Place cooked apples in center and fold over and seal with fork. Fry in oil, about 1 inch in skillet, turn over and fry until brown.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Saute beef, onion and green pepper in a large frying pan until beef is lightly browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain off fat; add flour to frying pan and stir well.
Add tomatoes and seasonings.
Combine noodles with meat sauce and put in 9 x 13 x 2-inch baking dish; top with the shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until heated through and bubbly.
Makes 8 to 10 servings.

title: almond bars
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients and pat into bottom of greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix the next 4 ingredients and pour over base.
Sprinkle with slivered almonds.
Bake for 40 minutes at 325°.
Chill and then cut into bars.

title: blueberry-orange nut bread
directions: Into a mixing bowl, sift first 5 ingredients. In another bowl, beat the eggs, milk, melted butter, orange zest and orange juice. Stir into flour mixture just until dry ingredients are moistened. Fold in blueberries and nuts. Pour batter into a greased loaf pan and bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes. Remove from pan. Cool. Wrap in foil and store overnight before cutting and serving.

title: peach pie
directions: Beat sugar, cream cheese and sour cream together.
Add Jell-O and beat.
Add Cool Whip, vanilla and peaches.
(Stir Cool Whip, vanilla and peaches by hand.)
Pour into crust and chill.

title: lisa's red beans and rice
directions: Cut your sausage up thin.
Saute in skillet and set aside. Cut up your onions, pepper and celery (coarsely) and saute in olive oil.
Add tomatoes, seasonings, tomato paste and sausage. Add mushrooms and beans last.
Cook long and slow on medium to low heat, not high heat.
Serve over rice with garlic bread.

title: chili
directions: Cook the garlic, onion and green pepper in the oil until soft. Add the beef and cook until lightly browned.
Add the tomato sauce and chili powder. Cover and cook slowly for 20 minutes.
Add the beans and simmer, uncovered, 20 to 25 minutes. Serve at once or make ahead and reheat.
Add water to thin. Can be frozen.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix well.
Store in airtight container.
Use 2 heaping teaspoons of mix (or to taste) in cup of boiling water.
Drink whenever you feel chilly.

title: apple-smothered pork chops
directions: You will need 2 sheets (18 x 24-inch each) Reynolds Wrap| heavy-duty aluminum foil.

title: cracker pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks and add to the milk.
Combine crackers with the egg and milk mixture.
Add 1/2 cup sugar, vanilla and coconut in a saucepan.
Cook until thickened.
Allow egg whites to reach room temperature, then beat gradually, adding the remaining 1/4 cup sugar.
Beat until stiff peaks form.
Spread egg whites on top of cracker pudding and place in 350° oven until delicately brown.

title: my favorite pickles(best of all, soooo easy)
directions: Mix white sugar, vinegar and celery seed.
Combine until sugar dissolves.
Take Vlasic dill pickles, drain, rinse and slice thin. Slice onions. Stir into sugar mixture and return to jar.
Roll jar until all sugar is dissolved.
Put in refrigerator and enjoy.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Fry hamburger and season with garlic powder and seasoned salt until crumbled.
Drain and discard grease.
With hamburger, add onions and peppers.
Saute for 5 minutes; mix in next ingredients (soup, beer, Worcestershire sauce, oregano, Tabasco sauce and tomatoes).
Reduce heat and simmer 30 minutes (partially covered). Stir occasionally.
Serve open-faced over heated buns.
Sprinkle on cheese.

title: scottish shortbread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°. Mix ingredients together; knead until consistency becomes doughy. Press into greased mold. Bake 45 minutes until lightly browned and springy to touch. Cool and turn out.

title: easy dumplings
directions: Mix ingredients together, pouring milk slowly into flour.
May not need a full cup.
Roll out on floured board.
Cut in pieces. Drop into boiling chicken broth.

title: christmas tea
directions: Note: All ingredients are dry.

title: monkey mix
directions: Note: Make this up in
a gallon size Ziploc bag and this will be a piece of cake!

title: chocolate pretzels
directions: Melt chocolate.
Roll or dip 2/3 of pretzel log in melted chocolate.
Roll in nonpareils.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Cook and bone chicken or use 4 or 5 chicken breasts.
Saute in butter the mushrooms, green pepper and onion.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Cook rice per directions on the box.
Cook the bacon and crumble it.
Combine the raisins and water.
Saute celery and onion for 10 minutes.
Combine all items and lay pork chops on top.
Bake at 300° for 20 minutes.

title: jello salad
directions: Put pineapple and jello in saucepan; heat to dissolve jello. Let mixture cool a little, then add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Mix with mixer and place in refrigerator.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix together.
Bake in a 325° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce to 300° for 35 minutes or until done.
Makes two 9-inch deep dish or 3 small crusts.

title: t.v. snacks
directions: Melt margarine.
Add Worcestershire sauce and salts.
Pour over all ingredients, which have been mixed, then mix well.
Bake at 350°, stirring every 10 minutes for about 30 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and beat well.
Pour into tube pan and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Cut meat into chunks.
Precook potatoes, onion, celery, peas and carrots until tender.
Drain. Add chicken broth and cream.
Cook over medium heat until mixture is thick enough to coat the back of a spoon.
Place one pie crust into the bottom of a deep dish pie pan.
Layer chicken and vegetables in the crust and top with sauce mixture.
Cover with second crust and make several slits in top of the crust.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.

title: mexican salad
directions: Line dish with Fritos.
Layer cooked rice, chili, cheese, onions, lettuce and tomatoes.
Serve immediately.

title: bloody mary
directions: Dissolve bouillon cubes in water.
Add other ingredients. Chill.
This can be served frozen.

title: chicken manicotti(entree)
directions: Shells:
Combine chicken/ mushroom soup and sour cream; mix well.
Add chicken to half of mixture.
Mix well.
Stuff this mixture into partially cooked manicotti shells.
Place stuffed shells in baking pan.

title: polish pickled eggs
directions: In a large bowl, combine the pickled beets and their juice with the vinegar, 4 cups water, garlic, bay leaf, pickling spices and salt.
Add boiled eggs and onion rings.
Cover and refrigerate for several days.

title: buttermilk layer cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening, 2/3 cup buttermilk and flavoring.
Beat about 1/2 minute at low speed, then 2 minutes at medium.
Add rest of buttermilk and eggs. Beat 2 more minutes. Makes 2 layers or 24 cupcakes.
Bake at 375° about 25 minutes.

title: ham and cheese tart
directions: Roll pie crust into a 13-inch circle; place onto a 12-inch pizza pan.
Fold edges under and crimp; prick with a fork.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes; cool.
Arrange 6 slices cheese, overlapping, on baked crust.
Sprinkle with cooked ham.
Cook onion in butter in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender.
Remove from heat.
Stir in eggs and next 3 ingredients.
Spoon over ham.
Cut each of the remaining 2 cheese slices into 9 squares.
Arrange on top.
Bake at 425° on lower rack of oven 15 minutes or until set.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Yields one 12-inch tart.

title: asparagus casserole 2
directions: Beat eggs.
Add salt and pepper, cracker crumbs, pimento, cheese and milk.
Pour over asparagus in a casserole dish.
Melt butter and pour over top of mixture.
Top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Mix together; pour into 1 crust and top with second crust. Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: breaded veal cutlets
directions: Dip veal into egg mixture; then crumbs.
Brown in hot fat. Pour over milk, mixed with soup, in baking dish.
Cover; bake in slow oven at 300° for 1 hour.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick.
Add sour cream and Cool Whip.
Alternate layers of bananas and wafers.
Spread pudding on each layer.
Put Cool Whip and sour cream on top.
Sprinkle with graham crackers or vanilla wafers.

title: beef barley stew(crock-pot)
directions: In a skillet, brown beef and onion in oil. Drain. Transfer to a 5-quart slow cooker. Add water, tomato sauce, carrots, celery, salt, oregano, paprika and pepper. Cover and cook on low for 4 to 5 hours. Add beans, corn and barley; cover and cook on low 2 hours longer or until barley, beef and vegetables are tender. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Drain artichoke hearts.
Chop up.
Put in bowl. Mix all ingredients together.
Put into ungreased pie plate.
Bake at 325° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes.
Bake until brown or bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: homemade hot chocolate
directions: Makes a big batch.
Excellent for Christmas.
Place lunch baggie full of homemade hot chocolate in green or red lunch bags for gifts.

title: leeann chin's stir-fried beef with broccoli
directions: Soak mushrooms in warm water until soft, about 30 minutes; drain.
Rinse in warm water; drain.
Remove and discard stems; cut caps into 1/2-inch pieces.
Trim fat from beef; cut beef with grain into 2-inch strips.

Cut strips across grain into 1/8-inch slices. Toss beef, 1 tablespoon oil, 1 teaspoon cornstarch, 1 teaspoon salt, sugar, soy sauce and white pepper in glass or plastic bowl. Cover and refrigerate 20 minutes.
Cut broccoli into 1-inch pieces. Cut lengthwise gashes in stems thicker than 1-inch.
Place broccoli in boiling water.
Cover and cook 1 minute.
Drain.
Immediately rinse under running cold water; drain.
Cut green onions into 2-inch pieces.
Mix 1/4 cup chicken broth, the oyster sauce and 2 tablespoons cornstarch.

title: chicken-apple salad
directions: Combine all ingredients, except lettuce.
Chill thoroughly. Serve on lettuce with potato chips and carrot sticks.
Two cups of cooked turkey or 2 (6 1/2 ounce) cans of tuna may be used instead of chicken.
Makes approximately 6 servings.

title: texas fudge
directions: Bring the sugar and milk to a boil slowly and cook about 15 minutes until a soft ball can be formed when dropping a little into cold water.
Have the other 5 ingredients all ready to add quickly and stir until it begins to thicken.
Pour onto 11 x 17 x 1-inch buttered cookie sheet.
Cool and keep refrigerated until ready to cut and eat.

title: plum pudding
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients in a bowl.
In a separate bowl, blend dry ingredients; add all together.
Grease a steam pan and cover thoroughly.
Place mixture in steam pan for 3 1/2 hours.
Serve with brandied hard sauce.

title: baked spaghetti
directions: Prepare the hamburger by boiling rapidly in enough water to cover meat. Break the meat up so as not to have lumps in the meat. Pour off water and repeat cleaning process. Add all ingredients. Simmer for 1 hour. Cook spaghetti until tender, enough to pinch in two. Add spaghetti to cold water to terminate cooking; drain. Layer mix in large casserole the sauce, spaghetti and sharp Cheddar cheese, ending with sauce. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Bake at 350° until sides are bubbling and top is browned.

title: minnesota punch
directions: Mix ingredients serve over ice.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix together potatoes, soup and sour cream.
Place in a 9 inch x 13 inch dish that has been sprayed with Pam.
Place cheese on top.
Bake at 350 degrees for 1 hour.

title: glorified chicken
directions: In a buttered casserole dish, place rice and chicken.
Mix in bowl together, the orange juice, sherry and cream of mushroom soup.
Pour this over the chicken and rice.
On top, sprinkle the French onion soup mix.
Cook covered for 2 hours at 350°.
Stir occasionally.

title: 150 year old oatmeal cookies
directions: Dissolve soda in water.
Mix ingredients; add the egg whites last.
This is a very stiff mixture, but do not moisten.
Drop with teaspoon 2 inches apart.
Bake in moderate oven (350° or so).

title: date nut balls
directions: Put the chopped dates, margarine, brown sugar and beaten eggs in a saucepan; cook, stirring constantly, over medium heat until mixture is very smooth and thick.
Then set aside to cool.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1 cup lukewarm water.
Dissolve sugar and lard in 1 cup boiling water.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast mixture, egg and then flour (a little at a time).
Let rise overnight in refrigerator.
Make into cloverleaf rolls or roll out and cut. Bake at 450° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: jam or jelly
directions: Cook berries or make juice.
Use 4 cups sugar to 5 cups juice or berries.
Cook in 5-cup amounts (about 25 to 30 minutes). Jelly is done when it flakes off in a metal spoon.
Stir often and watch closely.

title: apple pie
directions: Pare and core apples.
Slice thin and add cinnamon and sugar. Put in prepared crust and dot with margarine.
Put on top crust. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake for an additional 25 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Top the ingredients with 1 cup crushed saltine crackers. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes or until brown on top.

title: easy nut bread
directions: Combine sugar, egg, milk and nuts in mixing bowl; mix well. Stir in biscuit mix; beat vigorously for 1/2 minute.
Pour into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes (more or less).
Keep checking after 30 minutes.
Check for sides pulling away like cake, then it's done.

title: cry-baby cookies
directions: Mix as for butter cake, adding molasses after sugar, then beaten eggs.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir in chopped raisins and nuts.
Add some of flour mixture to sugar mixture, beat well, then add coffee and flour mixture, alternately.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake in 375° oven until done, about 15 minutes.
The children love these cookies and they are good for them, too.

title: marinated artichoke hearts with pasta in a creamy sauce
directions: Pour liquid from hearts into skillet.
Add oil, butter, onion and garlic; saute until soft.
Add hearts and basil and cook for five minutes (you may wish to cut hearts in half).
Take off heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour onto 1/2 to 3/4 pound cooked pasta and mix completely.
Enjoy!

title: kentucky wonder green beans vinaigrette
directions: Wash green beans and trim ends.
Arrange beans in a steamer basket and place over boiling water.
Cover and steam 8 to 10 minutes or until crisp-tender.
Plunge beans in cold water; drain. Combine beans, peppers and salad dressing.
Sprinkle with pepper. Cover and chill for 2 hours.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: caramel corn
directions: Combine all ingredients, except soda and popped corn. Bring to a boil over medium heat. Stir constantly. Boil rapidly for 5 minutes (soft boil stage). Remove from heat and stir in soda quickly. Pour over popcorn in a large pan and stir. Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring occasionally. Turn out on wax paper and break into clusters. Store in tightly covered containers.

title: lite tangy-cheese cauliflower(microwave oven)
directions: Prepare cauliflower by removing stem and greens.
Rinse under water but do not shake to dry.
Place in a microwave-safe dish. Cover loosely with waxed paper.
Microwave for 8 to 9 minutes on High (100%) or until tender.
Meanwhile, combine mayonnaise and mustard to make the tangy sauce.
Immediately spoon mustard sauce on top of cauliflower.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand 5 minutes until cheese melts.
Makes 8 servings.

title: holiday gingerbread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add egg and molasses.
Sift dry ingredients and add to mix.
Add hot water and beat until smooth. Pour in a greased and floured 9-inch pan; bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: cinnamon apple crisp
directions: Dissolve cinnamon drops in water over low heat.
Pour over apples and mix.
Turn into buttered 9-inch pan.
Mix flour, sugar and butter to coarse crumbs.
Spread over apples.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until apples are done.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix together.
Put in cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground chuck and onion; drain.
Add tomatoes and tomato paste, pepper, garlic, salt and Parmesan cheese.
Cook on low for 30 to 45 minutes.
Cook noodles while waiting for sauce.
Add cottage cheese after cooking.
Cover casserole dish with noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Keep layering sauce and cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fried stuffed jalapeno peppers
directions: Cut stems from peppers.
Remove seeds with small knife (do not split peppers).
Stuff with pimento cheese.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Combine 1/4 cup flour, 2 tablespoons cornmeal, salt, pepper and buttermilk; set aside.
Combine remaining flour and cornmeal.
Dip stuffed peppers in milk mixture, then dredge in flour mixture.
Pour oil to a depth of 2 to 3 inches.
Heat to 375°.
Fry peppers, a few at a time, for 1 to 2 minutes on each side or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels.
Makes about 12 peppers.

title: dr. bird cake
directions: Mix sugar and oil.
Add eggs and vanilla. Add dry ingredients and mix well.
Stir in by hand the coconut, pineapple, raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350° in a greased and floured tube pan for 1 1/2 hours.

title: holiday pound cake
directions: Beat eggs one at a time.
Add sugar, butter and flavoring. Put salt and soda in sifted flour.
Remove 1 cup flour to roll pecans and fruits in before combining in cake.
Add floured fruits and nuts and mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured Bundt or round cake pan.
Bake 3 hours at 250°.

title: easy chocolate cupcakes
directions: Beat all ingredients together.
Bake in cupcake tins at 325°.

title: great oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Add other ingredients in order listed.
Drop by tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° approximately 10 minutes.
Don't overbake. These are great for freezing.
Layer between wax paper or parchment, seal in airtight container.
Will keep a couple of weeks.

title: dynamite potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in jacket with bay leaf.
Cool completely.
Peel and grate.
Melt butter and add to can of cream of chicken soup. Mix until smooth.
Add sour cream, 1 cup grated cheese (reserve 1/2 cup), onion and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
The last 15 minutes, top with 1/2 cup crushed cornflakes and 1/2 cup grated cheese.

title: sausage
directions: Mix all together and shape like a sausage.
Wrap tightly in foil and refrigerate 24 hours.
Before baking, poke holes in foil. Bake on broiler pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: red cabbage
directions: Heat bacon drippings; add cabbage, apples, brown sugar, vinegar, water, salt and pepper.
Simmer, covered, for 15 to 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Yields 5 servings.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent roll dough on jelly roll pan.
Bake according to package directions.
Cool.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Mix well and chill overnight.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes for 20 to 30 minutes until tender.
Drain, cool and slice.
Fry bacon until crisp and drain.
In same skillet, saute onion.
Add flour, sugar, seasonings, vinegar and water, stirring until mixture begins to thicken slightly.
Add bacon, potatoes and crumble in eggs.

title: peach pudding
directions: Spray a 4-quart pan.
Cream 1 cup sugar and butter.
Add milk, flour and baking powder.
Stir together and pour in pan.
Add peeled, sliced peaches on top.
Dot with additional butter. Sprinkle 1 cup sugar over.
Pour boiling water over mixture.
Do not stir!
Bake at 375° for approximately 45 minutes.
Set pan on cookie sheet or foil in oven.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar; add eggs.
Sift flour, cocoa and salt together 3 times.
Add dry ingredients alternately to cream mixture with buttermilk and food coloring.
Beat well. Fold in soda and vinegar mixture.
Bake in 2 layers at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken kiev
directions: Pound out chicken breasts until 1/4-inch thick.
Melt butter. Add to melted butter, onion powder, oregano, parsley, salt and pepper to taste. (You may also use diced onions.)

title: turkey broccoli casserole
directions: Place 1/2 broccoli (cooked and well drained) on bottom of well buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Mix mayonnaise, cream of chicken soup, cheese and curry (be sure to mix curry with melted oleo).
Place 1/2 the turkey over broccoli and cover with 1/2 the mayonnaise, soup and cheese mixture.
Continue with remaining layers.
Top with buttered crumbs just before baking.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: layered dessert
directions: Melt margarine in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour in layers graham cracker crumbs, coconut, chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Pour can of condensed milk over this.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, butter and syrup together and cook to a rolling boil.
Then add peanuts.
Cook until peanuts start to pop.
Then cook 5 minutes.
Turn off heat, add baking soda and vanilla.
Pour in well-greased cookie sheet.
Cool, then break and eat.

title: pork chops baked in sour cream
directions: Dredge pork chops in bread crumbs.
Insert 1 clove slice into each chop. Brown lightly in oil.
Place in baking dish. Combine and heat all other ingredients.
Pour over chops. Bake, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve with rice.

title: cornbread tamale pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet. Add tomato soup, water, salt, pepper, chili powder, corn and green pepper. Simmer for 15 minutes.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Mix shortening
and peanut butter until smoothly blended. Cream in
sugar
gradually.
Stir in vanilla and slightly beaten eggs.
Sift
dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture in
3 portions.
Form
dough
in
1-inch
balls.
Place
on ungreased baking sheet.
Press balls down with floured fork so ridges remain in dough.
Bake
at 375° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Yield:
6 dozen.

title: yummy blueberry dessert
directions: Mix Jell-O, using only 2 cups of hot water.
Add pie filling and crushed pineapple.
Set aside to gel.

title: striped delight
directions: Mix all ingredients to make a crust.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: ranch style beans
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Stir in soup mix.
Add all other ingredients.
Put in 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes, until bubbly.
Serve with green salad, rolls and coffee.

title: turkey pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toss turkey with flour and cook onion, celery, thyme and pepper in margarine. Add carrots, water, soup, beans and turkey.
Pour into 2-quart casserole and put biscuits on top.
Bake 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: aunt bea's festive chicken salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine reserved juice and cream cheese; mixing until well blended.
Add pineapple and remaining ingredients, except tomatoes and mix lightly.
Chill.

title: winter fruit salad
directions: In a saucepan mix pineapple juice and pudding; cook until thickened and cool.
Toss and chill.
Cover with whipped topping.

title: pumpkin seeds
directions: Remove seeds from pumpkin.
Clean off all strings; rinse and drain.
Let seeds dry overnight in baking pan.
For every cup of seeds, melt 1 tablespoon butter with 1 teaspoon salt.
Mix all together and bake in very low oven, about 250°; cool.

title: turkey roulades
directions: Lay cutlets flat with narrow end towards you.
Spread cheese on each within 1/4-inch of edges.
Fold up long sides, about 1/4-inch.
Press into cheese.
Roll up from narrow end.
Coat each with flour; dip in egg, then roll in bread crumbs.
Arrange seam side down in greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Chill 30 minutes. Heat oven to 425°.
Drizzle melted butter over cutlets.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes until juices run clear when meat is pierced.

title: poppy seed bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients with mixer.
Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and remove from pans.
Yield: 2 loaves.

title: spicy spaghetti
directions: Mix all ingredients (not spaghetti) in a large pot and bring to boil.
Reduce heat and simmer covered 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Prepare spaghetti according to package.
Serve with meatballs.

title: sugared peanuts
directions: Over medium heat in heavy saucepan, cook sugar and and water until sugar is dissolved.
Add peanuts and cook, stirring frequently until liquid has turned to sugar coating.
Pour onto cookie sheet and bake at 300° for 30 minutes, stirring every 10 minutes.

title: fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla, crushed pineapple and grated lemon rind.
Combine raisins, citron peel, cherries and candied pineapple in large bowl.
Sift flour with baking powder and salt.
Cover fruit with flour mixture.
Be sure fruit is well covered.
Combine with first mixture and blend well. Spoon into
2 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) pans, which have been lined with greased brown paper.
Bake at 275° for 2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean and dry.
Turn out on racks to cool.
Ice when you wish.
Cakes may be used in a week.

title: stromboli
directions: Roll out dough to 12 x 16-inch rectangle.
Crumble cooked sausage evenly over dough.
Spread cheese over sausage.
Starting at end roll dough.
Pierce through with fork to allow steam to escape.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes until brown.
Cool. Slice into 1-inch sections.

title: 4-alarm chili
directions: Cook crumbled sausage, onion and garlic in hot oil until sausage is no longer pink.
Drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except Cheddar cheese, sour cream and green onions.
Simmer, uncovered, for 45 minutes.
To serve, top each bowl of chili with Cheddar cheese, a dollop of sour cream and green onions.
Makes 6 servings.

title: snackin' cake
directions: Combine the cake mix, eggs, milk, oil and frosting in a mixing bowl. Beat until blended. Pour into Bundt pan that has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: southern hash
directions: Brown onion and bell pepper in butter; remove from pan.
Brown ground beef until redness is gone.
Add onion, bell pepper, rice, tomatoes, salt, pepper and chili powder.
Pour into greased dish. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pie crust
directions: Let set for 20 minutes after mixing.
Press in pie pan and bake 7 to 10 minutes at 375°.

title: pizza turnovers
directions: Dissolve yeast in water. Stir in sugar, oil and 1 cup flour. Beat until smooth.
Mix in enough remaining flour to make dough easy to handle.
Knead until smooth and elastic (5 minutes).

title: homemade hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt butter and chocolate squares in a pan (low heat).
Once melted, add sugar and then can of Carnation milk. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until it thickens (sauce). Add vanilla. Tastes great on almost any flavor of ice cream!

title: pikes peak potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into greased 9 x 9-inch casserole.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Mix cream with chicken broth and pour over potatoes.
Cover and bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Uncover and bake another 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese and return to oven. Leave until cheese melts.

title: pizza loaf
directions: Cook macaroni; drain.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Add 1 1/2 cups of tomato sauce, oregano, macaroni and egg.
Place in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Top with strips of cheese and remaining sauce. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese for serving.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: peanut butter swirl bars
directions: In large bowl, combine peanut butter, butter, brown sugar and white sugar.
Beat until creamy.
Gradually beat in eggs and vanilla.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Blend well.
Spread into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle chocolate chips over top.
Place in 350° oven for 5 minutes; remove and run knife through to swirl; bake another 15 to 20 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix with stuffing.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Spread half of stuffing mixture on bottom of 9 x 12-inch pan or casserole dish.
Cover with chicken mixture and top with remaining stuffing.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
(Check the crumb mixture as it browns easily.)

title: peanut clusters
directions: In a glass bowl set the white bark and the chocolate chips. Cover and bake at 225° until melted (about 20 to 25 minutes). Remove from oven.
Mix in redskin peanuts until all peanuts are covered with chocolate.
Drop spoonfuls on wax paper.
May harden in refrigerator.

title: dreamy apricot salad
directions: Combine jello, sugar and water in a saucepan; bring to a boil, stirring until jello and sugar are dissolved.
Remove from heat. Stir in baby apricots and pineapple.
Let stand until cool.
Beat condensed milk and cream cheese with mixer until smooth.
Stir in jello mixture and nuts.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Chill overnight.
Serve with whipped topping.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter or spray 4 large loaf pans (9 x 5-inch) or 8 mini loaf pans (7 1/4 x 3 3/4-inches).
Stir together in a large bowl the first 5 ingredients.
Sift together the next 5 dry ingredients.
Add by the cupful to the other mixture; stir until well blended.
Add nuts and walnut oil; stir.
Spoon into pans and bake for approximately 1 hour.
Cool on racks.

title: best ever strawberry pie
directions: Mix all together. Boil 3 minutes. Let cool and then add 2 pints clean, fresh strawberries.
Pour into pie shell.
Chill several hours.
Then cover with 1 small Cool Whip.

title: salmon salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May add more or less of each ingredient, depending on taste and texture desired.
May substitute salmon and use instead of tuna in a tuna salad recipe.

title: meat pie
directions: Press out crescent rolls in glass pie pan to form pie crust and bake until done.
Brown hamburger, onions, green pepper and drain.
To hamburger mixture, add tomato sauce, pepperoni, chili hot beans and season with garlic powder and Italian seasoning. Simmer all together about 20 minutes on low-medium heat.
Layer in pie crust the meat sauce mixture, then Mozzarella cheese.
Top with a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until top cheese layer is very lightly browned.
Let cool and cut into pie slices.

title: butterscotch crisp balls
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over low heat.
Add marshmallows. Stir until butter is melted.
Remove from heat.
Add sugar-coated flakes.
Add butterscotch chips and coconut.
Mix well.
Roll into balls about 1 1/2-inches around with greased hands.
Allow to stand at room temperature until set, about 1 hour.
Makes about 3 dozen.
Very good.

title: swiss cheese chicken casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place the chicken breasts in a shallow Pyrex dish.
Mix the white wine and the chicken soup in separate bowl and set aside.
Place a slice of Swiss cheese on top of each chicken breast.
Pour the wine mixture over chicken and cheese. Spread an even layer of bread crumbs over the chicken.
Slice the butter into small sections and place on top of bread crumbs.
Cover with aluminum foil and bake for 45 minutes.
Uncover and continue to bake for 15 minutes.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, shortening, eggs, pumpkin and water together.
Add dry ingredients to pumpkin mixture and stir well.
Divide into 2 well-greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: no work chicken
directions: Place chicken snugly, skin side down, in flat baking dish in one layer.
Make marinade by mixing together remaining ingredients.
Pour over chicken and refrigerate for 6 hours or overnight.
When ready, turn chicken, cover dish with foil and bake at 350° for one hour.
Remove foil; baste well and continue baking, uncovered, for 15 more minutes.

title: possum pie
directions: Combine butter, pecans and flour.
Press into a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes.
Cool.
Combine cream cheese, powdered sugar and 1 cup of Cool Whip.
Beat well.
Spread on cooled crust.
Make puddings as directed, except reduce milk to 1 1/2 cups each.
Spread vanilla pudding on cream cheese layer. Spread chocolate pudding on top of vanilla layer.
Top with remaining Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with Heath or Crunch bar. Refrigerate.

title: mimi's peanut butter fudge
directions: In large, heavy saucepan over medium heat, stir together sugars and evaporated milk.
Stir until it starts to boil, then don't stir while it cooks to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Add marshmallow cream and beat well.
Add peanut butter and beat quickly, it will start to set up quickly after peanut butter is added.
Pour into buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
(Do not make this on a real rainy or humid day!)
When cool, cut in squares.
Store airtight.

title: eggless white cake
directions: Cream shortening with 1 cup sugar.
Sift together the flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Add alternately 1 cup buttermilk with dry ingredients to the shortening-sugar mixture.
Add the vanilla.
Pour in a greased, floured 8 1/2-inch square pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: fake pralines(very easy and delicious)
directions: Heat and stir butter and sugar over low flame.
Pour over graham crackers that are placed on a cookie sheet.
Put a nut on each square.
Heat in 350° oven for 10 minutes.
Take out and let cool until topping hardens.

title: calico beans casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Saute onion and celery.
Add bell pepper.
Add tomato soup, tomato paste and catsup.
Stir and simmer 15 to 20 minutes.
Add drained green, wax and lima beans and remaining ingredients.
Mix altogether; bake, uncovered, for 1 hour at 350°.
Serves 25.

title: cajun seasoning
directions: Mix all and store in shaker.
This is very good to sprinkle on soups and stews. Careful!
It's pretty powerful.
(I have made large amounts and given in decorated shakers for Christmas.)

title: easy cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese to room temperature.
Mix cheese with sugar, vanilla, egg (yolk only) and lemon juice.

title: grilled honey-glazed pork tenderloin
directions: Combine honey, oil, vinegar, garlic, herbs, salt and pepper in shallow pan. Add pork and turn to coat well. Cover and refrigerate 2 to 4 hours. Turn pork occasionally. Remove pan from the refrigerator 30 minutes before grilling.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender. Remove from pot and debone.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken until done and debone.
In a large pan cook macaroni and cheese, then drain.
Add butter and milk; mix well. Add cream of mushroom soup.
Add chicken and mix well.
Top with smashed crackers.
Put in a glass pan.
Bake at 325° for 15 minutes.

title: mustard dressing(for slaw)
directions: Mix together and cook over a slow fire until thick.
Mix with slaw.

title: chess cake
directions: Mix and press into 13x9x2 1/2 inch greased cake pan.

title: amish cabbage
directions: Chop and boil cabbage; drain and set aside.
Fry bacon; crumble and mix with cabbage.
Slice potatoes; cook in enough milk to cover.
Cook until soft.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together sour cream, potatoes, cabbage and bacon.

title: taco bake
directions: Brown ground meat in frying pan along with taco seasoning. Drain grease from pan.
Prepare corn bread mixes per instructions on box.
Pour corn bread batter into a greased 9x13 pan.
Bake at 375° for 10-15 minutes until lightly browned.
Spread meat over corn bread and sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Place pan back in oven until cheese melts. Spread shredded lettuce over melted cheese.
Sprinkle with diced tomatoes and garnish with sliced black olives. Serve with sour cream and salsa.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix all ingredients and let come to a boil.
Cook only until it begins to change color.
Put in jars and seal.
Do not overcook or they will not be crisp.

title: daddy's chicken casserole
directions: In a large casserole dish, spread layer of stuffing. Drain peas and spread 1/2 can over stuffing.
Spread layer of chicken over peas.
Spread cream of chicken soup over this.
Add remaining peas and top with celery soup.
Add small amount of chicken broth. Add remaining chicken and top with remaining stuffing. Bake for 20 to 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: bavarian cream
directions: Make gelatin and when slightly thickened, whip.
(I use quick set method on package.)
Fold in fruit, nuts and whipped cream until well combined.
Then put aside until set!

title: calico beans
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, bacon and onions.
Combine all in a 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour.
Serves 14.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Mix cranberry sauce
into
hot	jello
mixture and dissolve. When this cools
and starts to jell, add pineapple and nuts. Mold.

title: chocolate chip bars
directions: Heat oven to
Mix
margarine,
sugars
and
egg. Stir in flour (dough
will be stiff).
Stir in nuts and chocolate chips.
Press dough
in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan. Bake
until
golden
brown about 25 minutes; cool. Cut into bars. Yields about 24 bars.

title: my best fruit cake(all fruits and nuts)
directions: Mix coconut with nuts and fruit.
Add milk and mix thoroughly. Cook in paper lined cake tin at 250° for 2 1/2 hours.
Let cool in pan for 30 minutes.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar 5 minutes.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat 2 minutes.
Sift in flour, salt and soda.
Mix in oatmeal, chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by level tablespoons on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in a 350° oven for 14 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.

title: western cookies
directions: Mix butter with sugars.
Add egg and vanilla.
Add flour, cocoa, baking powder and soda.
Stir in oats, chips, raisins and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased sheet and bake at 375° for about 12 minutes.

title: apple salad
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients on low heat until thick, stirring constantly.
Set aside to cool.
When cool, stir in apples and pour into serving dish.
Cover with Cool Whip.

title: texas sheet cake
directions: Grease and lightly flour a 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine flour and sugar.
Measure into heavy saucepan, 2 sticks margarine, 7 tablespoons cocoa and water.
Heat to boiling, stirring well.
Add to flour-sugar mix and blend well.
In medium bowl, combine beaten eggs.
Stir soda into buttermilk.
Add to egg and vanilla.
Pour into flour mixture.
Add cocoa and pour into prepared pan.
Bake 25 minutes or until done.

title: elephant stew
directions: Cut elephant into small, bite size pieces.
This should take a month.
Add enough brown gravy to cover.
Cook over a kerosene fire for about 4 weeks at 465°.
This should serve 3800 people. If more are expected, 2 rabbits may be added, but do this only if necessary, as most people do not like hare in their stew!

title: beef tenderloin over rice
directions: Mix all ingredients together in casserole dish. Cover with lid and bake in oven for 4 hours at 250°. Serve over rice.

title: ice cream dessert
directions: Crust:
Combine 1 stick soft butter, 1/4 cup brown sugar, 1 cup flour and 1 cup chopped nuts; cook until golden brown at 350°, 15 to 20 minutes.
Stir often.
Cool.
Spread half on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: elegant chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter and shortening with sugar.
Add flavorings.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients and add to creamed mixture alternately with milk or sour cream.
Blend well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or test until done.

title: chicken rice-thumbolina's
directions: Mix rice, chicken, 2 beaten eggs, 1/2 can crushed tomato bits and 1/2 can cream of mushroom soup.
Mix ingredients well.
Place in greased molds (ovenproof).
Cover top with aluminum foil.
Place molds into larger pan and put 1 can water into larger pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: orange butter coffee cake
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl; let stand 5 minutes.
Add 1/4 cup sugar, stirring until dissolved.
Add salt, eggs, sour cream and 1/4 cup butter to yeast mixture; beat at medium speed of an electric mixer until blended.
Gradually stir in enough flour to make a soft dough.
Place in a well-greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover; let rise in a warm place (85°), free from drafts, 2 hours, or until doubled in bulk.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel and slice the apples to fill the pan a little over half full.
Sprinkle some sugar over the apples.
Top with the remaining mixture which is crumbly.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
If cheese is used, mix it in the topping.

title: carter cookies
directions: Melt crunchy peanut butter in microwave.
Add the chocolate bark.
Melt in microwave on Simmer setting 2 minutes at a time, stirring after each 2 minutes until melted.
Add nuts, cereal and marshmallows; stir until well coated with chocolate mixture.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.

title: apple crisp
directions: Put apples into buttered pan.
Mix flour, soda, salt, butter, brown sugar and oats.
Sprinkle over apples and bake for 15 minutes.

title: upside-down caramel apple pie
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Line pie plate, 9 x 1 1/4-inch, with a 14-inch circle of foil.
Spread 2 tablespoons margarine over foil. Press pecan halves, rounded sides down, on foil; sprinkle with brown sugar.

title: mexican spoon bread
directions: Mix together everything but chili and cheese.
Put half of mixture in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Put chili and 1/2 of the cheese on the mixture in the pan.
Add the rest of the corn mixture.
Sprinkle remaining cheese and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: banana caramel bars
directions: Combine flour, sugar and baking powder in a bowl. Cut in margarine with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal. Slowly stir in egg, mixing with a fork until crumbly.
Pat half of mixture in 13 x 9-inch baking pan to form crust.

title: easy canned grape juice
directions: Wash Concord grapes; pick from stems.
Into a clean quart jar, put 1 to 2 cups grapes.
(I usually use 1 1/2 cups grapes.)
Do not skin or seed.
Add 3/4 to 1 cup sugar.
Fill jar to overflowing with boiling hot water; partially seal.
Process in 275° oven for 30 minutes; complete the seal.
The juice is ready to drink after 6 weeks standing.
Strain the grapes from the liquid.
You can eat the grapes or make a pie out of them.
The juice has a particularly fresh sparkling flavor.
(This is a 50's recipe from high school economics book.)

title: chicken casserole
directions: Parboil chicken with celery and onion.
Lay chicken in casserole and cover with noodles, then soup.
Add milk, creamed corn, peas, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Cover with bread crumbs and put butter on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and bake another 10 minutes.

title: mississippi pecan pie
directions: Boil syrup and sugar together for 2 minutes; cool. Pour slowly over eggs, beating constantly. Add butter, vanilla and nuts. Pour into pie shell. Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 45 minutes or until done.

title: hot taco dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and spread in an 8 x 8-inch pan.
Mix chilies and taco sauce, then spread over cream cheese.
Sprinkle Mozzarella over top, then heat until bubbly.
Dip with plain Tostitos.

title: rice balls
directions: Boil rice.
When almost dry, add eggs, pepper and parsley. Let cool.
Shape balls and roll in crumbs.
Fry in olive oil until brown.

title: barbecued meatballs
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients well and shape into balls the size of a quarter and brown lightly.

title: one dish meal
directions: Saute meat and onion until meat is barely cooked.
Spray a 17 x 13-inch pan with "Pam".
Put meat and onion mixture in bottom and spread to sides.
Pour tomatoes over meat mixture.
(I don't use all of the juice.)
Then spread the drained corn and the previously made mashed potatoes.
(Make according to directions on bag, using the softer recipe.)

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut bread dough into small pieces.
Place in a tube or Bundt pan.
Add in layers the remaining ingredients.
To bake for breakfast, cover with foil and place in oven overnight to let dough rise.
Set time to bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: tomatoes provencale
directions: Cut tomatoes in half and press gently to remove seeds and water, season with salt and pepper.
Mix together remaining ingredients and spread cut sides of tomatoes with this mixture. Sprinkle tops with melted butter or salad oil.
Arrange on a heatproof serving dish and cook in a hot oven of 450° or under a broiler 10 to 15 minutes or until tomatoes are soft and tops are browned.

title: pepper slaw
directions: Combine vinegar, water, sugar and salt.
Add to shredded cabbage the diced peppers and celery seed.
Toss to mix thoroughly, then add vinegar mixture and let stand in a cold place several hours.

title: tangy corn
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan; cook over medium heat for 5 minutes or until heated through.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: german icebox slaw
directions: In a large bowl, alternate layers of shredded cabbage and onion rings.
In a saucepan, boil together remaining ingredients and pour over cabbage and onion mixture.
Let stand 4 to 8 hours in refrigerator before serving.
The slaw may be kept in the refrigerator as long as 3 weeks.

title: italian vegetable soup
directions: Combine ingredients, except margarine, in 4-quart dish.
Cover and microwave on High about 50 to 60 minutes. Stir every 15 to 20 minutes until spaghetti is tender. Add margarine.

title: crunchy pea salad
directions: Combine all ingredients. Chill. Garnish with bacon bits just before serving.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Cream sugar and eggs together.
Add fruit cocktail.
Sift together flour and baking soda; add to mixture.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar and walnuts over batter.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Use 2 (13 x 9 x 2-inch) pans.

title: pumpkin date nut bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar gradually.
Add eggs; beat well.
Blend in water, pumpkin and sifted dry ingredients.
Fold in pecans and dates.
Pour into 2 greased 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch loaf pans. Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: gold coast special tidbits
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Bring 2 cups water to boil.
Add scallops and bring to second boil.
Drain scallops.
In shallow casserole dish cube and layer 1 package of cream cheese.
Add layer of all the scallops.
Top with other package of cream cheese.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil and bake 15 minutes in 375°
oven. Remove foil and bake additional 5 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: raw potato hot dish
directions: Brown beef and onion. Drain fat. Add raw potatoes, celery and soup.
Place in 3-quart casserole and cover. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: no bake butterscotch bars
directions: Grease 9 x 12-inch pan and press crumbs, marshmallows, coconut and nuts in pan.
In another pan, beat eggs.
Add sugar and margarine.
Cook.
Pour cooked mixture over crumb mixture.
Melt peanut butter and butterscotch bits over low heat.
Place on top of other mixtures.

title: german chocolate upside-down cake
directions: I remember a molasses cake Grandma Rogers made when I was a little girl.
I would set on the bench by the kitchen table and say, "Grandma, how do you cook a cake?"

As I remember, she would put enough flour to fill a skillet half full, enough salt and soda to make it rise and enough molasses to make it real sweet, a big hunk of butter and maybe a little milk if the batter was too thick. Then she would pour this in an iron skillet and fire up the wood stove until it was pretty warm and cook it until it was done.
Then she would say, "Run tell Grandpa the cake is done."

title: cherry mountain pie
directions: Melt margarine in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Mix sugar, flour, baking powder and milk.
Pour batter over margarine in pan and add to center of batter the pie mix.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: greek salad
directions: Place romaine in plastic bag.
Fasten bag and refrigerate no longer than 24 hours.
Add remaining ingredients to bag.
Fasten bag securely and shake until well coated.

title: quick sticky buns
directions: In 8 or 9 inch layer pan, melt margarine in preheated oven. Remove from oven and stir in brown sugar, cinnamon, syrup and nuts. Place biscuits on top. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until biscuits are well browned. Let stand for 5 minutes. Invert on serving plate and remove pan.

title: onion souffle
directions: Mix together well.
Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes. Serve with chips, crackers or bread.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown the sausage meat.
Add the onions and green peppers; fry a little longer to brown onions and peppers.
Add the Ranch Style beans, pork and beans, brown sugar, ketchup, mustard and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix all together and put in crock-pot for several hours, until bubbly.
Or put in baking dish and bake in oven at 350° until it bubbles.

title: mama's easy squash casserole
directions: Boil sliced squash until tender.
Drain.
Place in baking dish.
Combine other ingredients except cracker crumbs and pour over squash, then put cracker crumbs on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: tortilla rolls
directions: With electric mixer, beat ham and cream cheese together until smooth.
Stir in pineapple, green onion and honey.
Spread 1/4 cup ham mixture on each flour tortilla to within 1/2-inch of edge. Roll up each tortilla starting from one edge; wrap in plastic wrap and refrigerate 2 to 8 hours before serving.

title: savory turkey loaf
directions: Beat together egg, applesauce, salt, poultry seasoning and pepper in large bowl.
Add turkey, wheat germ and onion.
Mix lightly.
Shape into loaf in shallow pan.
Sprinkle with paprika.

title: jeanette's hot clam dip
directions: Melt butter in frypan.
Saute onion and garlic.
Add clams and lemon juice and bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add everything, except cheese.
Mix well and put in a pie plate. Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.
Spread on Ritz crackers.

title: egg salad
directions: Remove
the
shells
from the hard-boiled eggs and chop fine. Add
the celery, sugar and salt; begin to add the salad dressing gradually
until there is a smooth mixture (a little more, or
a little less may be desired.) Let cool and serve as a sandwich
or as a salad on a bed of lettuce.
Serves 6 to 8 people.

title: easy sausage balls
directions: Crumble the sausage and mix with cheese. Add biscuit mix, one cup at a time. Form into small balls (about 1 inch in diameter); place on an ungreased cookie sheet. Bake in a preheated 350° to 375° oven until light brown (13 to 15 minutes). Can be prepared in advance and frozen, uncooked.
Cooking may take a few extra minutes if balls are frozen.
Makes about 7 dozen.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Cook chicken and cut up in chunky pieces.
Cook and drain broccoli as directed on box.
Grease casserole with butter.
Put broccoli in bottom of casserole and chicken on top of broccoli. Mix soup and mayonnaise; pour over chicken and broccoli.
Cut up slices of bread into cubes and cover top of dish.
Dot with butter and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
If bread browns too fast, lightly cover with foil.

title: sourdough scones
directions: In a medium bowl, combine the flours, 3 tablespoons sugar, baking powder, soda, orange peel, lemon peel and currants.
With a pastry blender, work in the butter until fine crumbs are formed. Add the sourdough starter; stir with a fork until dough holds together.
Form the dough into a ball and knead briefly, only until ingredients are combined.
Cut the dough into two equal parts; shape each half into a ball.
Flatten into a 5-inch circle, leaving dough slightly higher in the center.
Cut each circle into 6 wedges.
Sprinkle scones with remaining tablespoon of sugar.
Place them on ungreased baking sheet; bake in the middle of a preheated 375° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Add grits and salt to water and cook until thick.
Cool 15 minutes.
Melt margarine and cheese roll and add to grits.
Beat eggs with milk and slowly stir into grits.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole and top with crumbs or cheese.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: new england fish chowder
directions: Simmer haddock, covered, in boiling water 15 minutes.
Drain, reserving broth. Remove bones from fish. Saute diced pork until crisp.
Remove and set aside. Saute onion slices in pork drippings until golden brown. Add fish, potato, celery, bay leaf, salt, onion and pepper.
Pour in fish broth plus enough additional boiling water to make 1 1/2 cups liquid. Simmer, covered, 30 minutes. Add milk and butter; simmer 5 minutes more.
Serve chowder sprinkled with diced pork.
Makes 4 servings.

title: hot reuben dip
directions: In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese, sour cream and ketchup until smooth. Stir in the corned beef, sauerkraut, Swiss cheese and onion until blended. Transfer to a greased 1-quart baking dish. Cover and bake at 375° for 30 minutes. Uncover; bake 5 minutes longer or until bubbly. Serve warm with bread or crackers.

title: roquefort dressing
directions: Have cheese warm.
Combine cheese with 1 cup buttermilk and beat in electric mixer until smooth.
Then add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Chill before serving.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 2-quart casserole.
Mix all ingredients.
Pour into casserole.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Cook noodles; drain.
Brown hamburger; drain.
In mixing bowl add meat and cheese.
Stuff shells with meat mixture.
Pour sauce over shells.
Pour into baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: homemade pancakes
directions: Mix eggs, milk and oil. Mix remaining ingredients. Mix together and bake on griddle.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Mix together 2 cans of mushroom soup, 2 cans of chicken soup, 1 can Ro-Tel, 1 cup chicken broth, and 1 small chopped onion. Layer Dorito chips, soup mixture, and cheese. Start over. Top with shredded cheese. Bake 30 minutes at 350 or until brown.

title: apple dessert
directions: Put yellow cake mix, margarine and coconut in bowl and mix. Pat into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Mix sugar, cinnamon and apples and put over baked crust.
Blend the sour cream and egg; drizzle over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: easy caramel frosting
directions: In a large skillet, combine margarine and sugar.
Place over medium
heat
and
cook, stirring constantly, until sugar melts and
syrup
is
light
golden brown.
Add milk, stirring constantly.
(The
mixture
will
tend
to
lump,
but becomes smooth with further cooking.) Cook over medium heat, stirring, until a small
amount
dropped into a small bowl of cold water forms a
soft
ball.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla.
Beat to almost
spreading consistency.
Spread on your favorite chocolate or yellow cake which has been cooled.

title: peanut salad
directions: Add mayonnaise to other ingredients according to how creamy you want it.

title: taffy apple dip
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve on sliced Granny Smith apples.

title: grandma svensson's swedish pancakes
directions: Stir ingredients until smooth.
Add one more cup of milk.
Melt dab of oleo in hot large frypan.* Put about 1/4 cup of batter into pan.
Swirl batter to cover bottom of pan (pancake will be thin). Fry until lightly brown, then brown other side.
(This doesn't take very long.)
Roll pancake over knife blade.
Keep warm on plate over pan of boiling water.
Serve with butter, syrup or preserves.

title: peanut brittle
directions: In large glass bowl, mix corn syrup, sugar and water. Microwave on High for 4 1/2 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Add peanuts; microwave on High for 5 more minutes.
Remove and add margarine, salt, soda and vanilla.
Turn out quickly and spread on greased cookie sheet.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Combine chicken, the three cans of soup and one can of rotelli. Crush Doritos in to small bits.
Add Doritos to first mixture.
Put it in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: peach slump
