Drop by spoonfuls onto a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes.
Remove from sheet and cool.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: spinach dip for hollowed out bread
directions: Cut top of bread off; cut out inside of bread to form bowl. Use top and inside to make wedges to spread dip on. You will probably need to double recipe for most loaves.

title: fried pies
directions: Cut Crisco into flour; add sugar and salt.
Mix together egg and evaporated milk; add to flour mixture and mix well.
Chill in refrigerator overnight, if possible, before rolling out.

If you don't want to make this many pies at one time, you may shape into balls and roll each in a circle onto a square of waxed paper. Stack them with a section of wax paper between each circle and then freeze in tight container.
As you want to serve up a few fresh hot fried pies, remove as many circles as you like and allow to thaw on its own wax paper.
Put your fruit on 1/2 of the circle and fold over.
Be sure the crust is thawed before attempting to fold or you will break it.
Seal the edges and deep fry in hot oil.
This is important.
Turn only once and drain on paper towels.

title: hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion in pan with Pam.
Add beef.
Cook until browned. Add drained beans and soup.
Pour into greased casserole.
Spoon mashed potatoes over top.
(Add a bit of grated onion to potatoes if desired.)
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar and milk in saucepan and cook to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.

title: breaded tofu cutlets
directions: Drain water and cut each piece of tofu lengthwise, then crosswise.
Place between absorbent paper towels and allow to dry for several minutes.
Gently dust tofu, one piece at a time, with flour, then dip in egg and roll in bread crumbs.
Allow to dry for 10 to 15 minutes; top off an excess crumbs.

title: best ever meat loaf
directions: Break eggs into large mixing bowl; beat slightly with fork. Add milk, salt, pepper and crumbled bread.
Beat until bread has disintegrated.
Add onion, carrot, cheese and beef; mix well.
Pack into a loaf pan.
Combine brown sugar, catsup and mustard.
Spread over surface of loaf.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour.
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Lift the loaf out.
Slice and serve.

title: apple pizza
directions: Measure the flour, sugar and cinnamon into small bowl. Mix well. Press or roll biscuits into flat circles and place on lightly greased (or Pam spray) cookie sheet. Use tablespoon to depress center of biscuits to form pizza-like crust.

Lightly sprinkle brown sugar mixture on biscuits. Spoon grated apples on biscuits, then sprinkle with grated cheese if desired. Top with more of the brown sugar mixture and dot with butter. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Cook cabbage and onions in small amount of water (do not overcook).
Put in vegetable oil, cream of celery soup, sugar and salt and pepper to taste.
Put in casserole dish and cover with Pepperidge Farm herbal stuffing with 1 stick margarine.
Bake until bubbly and golden brown at 350° to 400°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Cream first 2 ingredients together well.
Sift next 4 ingredients together and add alternately with next ingredient. Follow Solomon's advice for making a good boy Proverbs 23:14.
Add next 3 ingredients.
Fold in beaten yolks and stiffly beaten whites carefully.

title: cinnamon hard candy
directions: Boil sugar, water and Karo syrup in a heavy pan to 300° (hard crack stage); add oil and color.
Remove from heat.
Line cookie pan with aluminum foil.
Pour in candy and place in freezer.
When set, break in pieces and toss in powdered sugar.

title: dump cake
directions: Mix pie filling and pineapple in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle nuts over top of filling.
Dump dry cake mix on top and spread evenly.
Slice butter and place evenly on top of cake mix.
Bake at 350° for about an hour or until golden brown.

title: christmas ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water; add ginger ale and lemon juice. Pour into 4-quart glass baking dish or mold.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill until almost firm.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
May freeze if desired (may leave bananas out).

title: onion salad dressing
directions: In blender, mix first 7 ingredients.
Slowly add oil.
Most of the time, I also add some catsup.
Blend.

title: english pea salad
directions: Drain peas.
Toss together the desired amounts of all ingredients and serve.

title: pie pastry
directions: Cut lard and flour into small balls.
Add water and salt and mix.
Roll out dough 1/8-inch thick.
Spread over and pat into desired size pie pan.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Beat the cream cheese and sugar.
Spray or butter a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Unroll crescent rolls, but don't separate.
Press onto bottom of pan.
Spread cream cheese mixture over crust. Place second can of rolls on top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Cream until fluffy oleo, oil, sugar and vanilla.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well.
Add alternately with 7-Up to mixture. Grease pan or use Pam spray to coat pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes, using tube or Bundt pan.

title: peanut butter crunch icing
directions: In top of double boiler, combine eggs, sugar, water and tartar.
Cook over boiling water for 7 minutes or until holds in peaks while beating constantly with rotary egg beater.
Remove; beat until cool.
Sprinkle with crushed peanut brittle over top of frosted cake.

title: wilma's christmas candy
directions: Mix buttermilk, sugar and soda together in saucepan.
Cook until brown and forms a soft ball in cold water.
Remove from heat and add vanilla and butter.
Beat until glossy.
Add pecan meats; stir until thick.
Spoon out onto wax paper and cool.

title: heath bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl with electric mixer, beat butter well; blend in brown sugar, egg yolk and vanilla.
By hand, mix in flour, 2/3 cup Heath bars and nuts.
Press into ungreased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2-inch jellyroll pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until browned.
Remove from oven and immediately sprinkle remaining Heath bars over top.
Cool slightly; cut into bars while warm.

title: fabulous fruit cup
directions: Combine pudding mix with fruit and juice in bowl.
Blend in sour cream.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 5 to 6 hours. Check after 4 hours. Mash with potato masher.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together corn bread mix, eggs, sour cream and margarine. Fold in the corns.
Pour into a greased 9 x 9-inch or casserole dish and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes until lightly brown. Remove from oven and sprinkle with shredded cheese.

title: sweet potato surprise
directions: Add potatoes and cream.
Be careful not to use too much cream. Add sugar, salt, beaten egg and coconut.
Let stand until cool. Press a marshmallow into the center of a portion of potato mixture and form into a ball.
Roll in bread crumbs and fry in deep oil. Drain on paper towels and serve while still hot.

title: jello-cottage salad
directions: Mix dry jello with cottage cheese.
Add pineapple and oranges. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill overnight before serving.

title: custard pie
directions: Let pie shell chill while making the filling.
Blend eggs, sugar, salt, vanilla and almond extract.
Gradually stir in scalded milk.
Pour into chilled, unbaked pie shell.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: boiled cookies
directions: In a saucepan, mix the sugar, cocoa, margarine and milk.
Heat to boiling.
Boil gently for 1 1/2 minutes.
Remove from heat. Beat in peanut butter, vanilla and oatmeal.
When blended, drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Drain tuna.
Make cream of mushroom soup as directed on can. Break up tuna and mix well in soup.
Cook noodles as directed on package.
Put in peas.
Drain noodles.
Pour mixture over noodles. Place in slightly greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook pasta according to package.
Rinse in cold water.
Add mayonnaise, ranch dressing, diced tomatoes, black olives, salt, pepper, and crumbled bacon.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 hour or longer.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons butter. Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar. Cream remaining butter and sugar. Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition. Add vanilla. Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixture. Beat well. Dredge peaches with remaining flour. Fold peaches into batter and pour into tube pan. Bake for 1 hour and 10 minutes. Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan.

title: salted pecans
directions: Melt butter in a large skillet; add pecans and salt.
Stir well to coat pecans; remove from heat.
Place pecans in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 200° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.
Drain on paper towels.
Yields 4 cups.

title: corn beef log
directions: Mix all ingredients well with hand mixer. Roll into a log and pat on chopped nuts.

title: aunt debbie's cloverleaf rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water in a large bowl.
Add sugar, shortening, egg, salt and half the flour; beat at low speed of electric mixer until smooth.
Stir in enough of the remaining flour to make a soft dough.
Place dough in a greased bowl, turning to grease top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place, free from drafts, 1 hour or until doubled in bulk.

title: cherry squares
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, creaming at medium speed until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating well after each.
At low speed, add flour and vanilla.
Pour into well-greased 15 x 10-inch jelly roll pan with sides.
Spread batter evenly.
Mark off into 48 squares.
Place one/two cherries with a little filling into middle of each square.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes. Cut while warm.
When cool, sift confectioners sugar over top.

title: robbie's peanut butter candy
directions: Mix with hands all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Press into a cookie sheet.
Melt chocolate chips and spread over top of base.
Cut into squares when hard.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel and cook potatoes until soft.
Mash with onion salt and sour cream.
Add butter to mixture.
Place in 2-quart casserole dish and top with cheese.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop all ingredients in blender. Add cream cheese and Accent to mixture.
Shape into large ball.
Wrap and refrigerate.
Let set for several hours before serving.

title: apple and sweet potato dish
directions: Slice sweet potato and apples very thin.
Layer, sprinkle cinnamon and dot with butter over each layer.
Cook in microwave or conventional oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: amish swiss steak
directions: Pound flour into steak.
Season with salt and pepper.
Brown in oil on both sides.
Place in roasting pan.
Slice 3 to 4 onions over meat.
Pour bottle of ketchup over top and fill water in roaster to cover meat.
Bake for 3 to 3 1/2 hours at 350°. Ingredients make a delicious gravy.
I serve with mashed potatoes and tossed salad.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine sugar, cream, milk, butter, corn syrup and salt in heavy 2-quart saucepan.
Stir over moderate heat until sugar is dissolved and mixture reaches a boil.
Boil 9 or 10 minutes (soft ball).
Remove from heat and let stand until lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat until mixture begins to lose its gloss. (Requires little beating.)
Quickly stir in walnuts and cherries. Turn into oiled pans.
Let stand until firm.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Whip up instant pudding using 3 cups milk.
When it is thick, fold in Cool Whip.
Line oblong pan with a layer of graham crackers.
Pour half the pudding mixture over crackers.
Put another layer of graham crackers over poured pudding and pour remaining pudding mixture over these crackers.
Cover with another layer of graham crackers and chill overnight.
Before serving, frost cake with chocolate frosting (ready made).

title: broccoli omelet
directions: Beat eggs in a bowl until light and fluffy.
Stir in broccoli, onion, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, milk, salt, basil and garlic powder.
Pour into ungreased 11 x 7 x 2-inch baking dish. Sprinkle 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese on top and place tomato wedges on top.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° until set, 25 to 30 minutes.

title: hot tomato starter
directions: Combine soups, water, and herbs in a large saucepan. Simmer 2 minutes. Dot with butter. Top each cupful with toasted saltine and a bit of parsley.

title: corn pudding
directions: Butter casserole pan; mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until lightly brown.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Mix well and bake 2 hours at 300° to 325°.

title: sweet n' sour meatballs
directions: Soak bread in bouillon.
Mash bread into meat.
Pour barbecue sauce and sweet n' sour into frying pan and mix thoroughly.
Form meat into 1-inch balls and dip into cold sauce.
Heat sauce on low heat and cook meatballs, turning until all sides are cooked. Simmer in sauce for about 2 hours or until sauce has become thick, dark and glazed.
Stir occasionally.
Drain off fat.
May be frozen and reheated.

title: turkey hash brown casserole
directions: Brown meat; drain if necessary.
Place in bottom of casserole dish.
Mix together onion, soup and drained vegetables.
Place in casserole.
Top with hash browns.
Bake at 350° until hash browns are done and casserole is heated through.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Mix sugar, butter, salt, egg and vinegar.
Add coconut, pecans and raisins.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: where's the beef?
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Add 3 dashes of Tabasco.
Place in buttered 11 x 7 baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: quick devil dogs
directions: Sift together flour, salt, soda, cocoa, sugar and baking powder.
Add milk, shortening and egg (nutmeats if desired). Batter will be cake like.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 5 to 7 minutes.
Can be frosted, sandwiched or plain.
Kids love them.

title: cranberry dessert
directions: Cream the butter and sugar until light.
Add eggs and beat until fluffy.
Fold in chopped nuts.
Spread over crumb layer.

title: salmon log roll
directions: Drain and flake salmon; remove all bones.
Combine salmon with next 6 ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Chill for one day.
Then mold by hand in a log shape and roll in pecans, salt and parsley mixture.
Make design on top of log roll with sliced green olives with pimento centers, and surround log roll on tray with fresh parsley to accent same.

title: turtle cake
directions: Melt caramels and 1/4 cup evaporated milk.
Keep warm.
Mix cake mix, butter and 3/4 cup evaporated milk.
Place a little less than half the cake mixture in a greased 9 x 12-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Pour melted caramels over cake and sprinkle nuts and chips on top.
Spread other half of cake mixture over the top and bake for 15 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Cook beans until
tender.
Fry	bacon.	Pour off excess grease.
Add rest
of
ingredients and mix well.
Add to beans and bake until heated through.

title: vegetable dip(makes 4 cups)
directions: Serve with fresh vegetables.
Recipe can be cut in half and makes 2 cups. Good for 2 weeks.

title: cheesecake cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, nuts and flour together in a bowl.
Stir in melted butter and mix with your hands until light and crumbly. Remove 1 cup of mixture to be used later as a topping.
Place remainder in an 8-inch square pan and press firmly.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 16 cookie squares.

title: spinach balls
directions: Cook spinach according to package directions and drain well. Combine with other ingredients.
Form into 1-inch balls and place on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Chill several hours.
Bake in 325° oven for 25 to 30 minutes.
(May be frozen before baking.) Makes approximately 36 balls.

title: cherry-cheese delight
directions: Combine cream cheese and sour cream.
Place layers of cream cheese mixture and cherry pie filling in sherbet glasses. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix together; put in a greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes; remove from oven.
Rub with butter or margarine; put back in oven to brown for 15 minutes more.

title: almost sugarless banana pudding
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Add crackers, pineapple and bananas.
Top with whipped topping; put in refrigerator.

title: squash pickles
directions: Soak squash, onion and bell pepper in salt, covered with 3 quarts cold water for at least 1 hour.
Drain well.

title: fruit and cheese dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruits in blender until smooth, about 1 minute.
Cover; chill 3 to 4 hours.
To serve, mound cheese dip in small bowl and place on tray and surround with fruits.

title: men's favorite meat casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and green pepper; add remaining ingredients except cheese.
Place in large flat pan; sprinkle with cheese.
Let stand overnight to allow flavors to blend.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Yields 15 servings.

title: crunchy vegetable salad
directions: Combine vegetables in a large bowl.
Pour salad dressing over and toss to coat evenly. Refrigerate until serving time.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: dorito salad
directions: Mix onion, lettuce and Cheddar cheese.
Add dressing and hot sauce to taste.
Crush and add Doritos chips.
Slice avocado and add to ingredients.
Brown ground meat and add kidney beans and 1/4 teaspoon salt; simmer 10 minutes, then add to cold salad.

title: rice casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice as directed on box. Saute onions in margarine until done. Cook broccoli as directed on package and drain. Mix together broccoli, soup, rice, onion, butter or margarine and cheese. Season with salt and pepper to taste. Place in a 9 x 13-inch ovenproof dish. Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sullivan's island shrimp
directions: Cook bacon in frying pan until crisp; remove.
Add butter, onion and celery to grease in pan; saute until tender.
Transfer bacon and this mixture to large pot.
Add remaining ingredients (except shrimp, cracker crumbs and sherry); cook slowly for 2 hours, until mixture thickens.
Add raw shrimp; cook until shrimp are done.
Add cracker crumbs and sherry; serve with fluffy rice. Serves 16.

title: squash patties
directions: Place squash in colander.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let set until all moisture is drained.
Then add other ingredients and form in patties; fry in deep fat.

title: flank steak marinade
directions: Combine oil, vinegar and seasonings in shallow glass pan. Brush both sides of flank steak with marinade.
Let stand in mixture 2 hours.
Broil 3 to 5 inches from heat for 5 minutes. Turn.
Brush with remaining marinade and broil another 4 minutes. Slice steak diagonally across grain as thin as possible.
Spoon pan juices over meat.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix well and pour into Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: spinach dip
directions: Thaw, drain and chop spinach.
Mix with other ingredients. Scoop out middle of a round pumpernickel loaf of bread.
Put dip inside.
You can use a container the size of hole in bread to put your dip in.
Dip assorted kinds of bread or crackers.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients into bowl.
Add salt and pepper.
Grease a casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: crab quiche bake
directions: In a bowl, combine all ingredients.
Transfer to a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until a knife inserted near the center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before cutting.
Yield:
6 to 8 servings.

title: molded cranberry waldorf
directions: Pour 1 cup cranberry juice in a saucepan and bring to a boil; add gelatin, stirring until dissolved.
Stir in remaining cranberry juice and salt.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold apple, celery and nuts into gelatin mixture.
Pour into a 4 cup mold or 6 individual molds.
Chill until firm.
Unmold and top with mayonnaise, if desired.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix together and let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: squash casserole
directions: Drain cooked squash and add margarine, salt and pepper, jalapeno and milk.
Mix and add beaten eggs, onions, cheese and cracker crumbs.
Pour into greased casserole.
Bake uncovered at 375° for about 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Mix Cool Whip and softened cream cheese until fluffy.
Blend in lemon juice; add condensed milk.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crusts; top with cherry pie filling.
Chill.

title: scalloped tomatoes
directions: Combine tomatoes, bread cubes and onion.
Heat butter, flour and seasonings in microwave until butter has melted.
Add to tomatoes and pour into a greased casserole.

title: fruit cake
directions: In a bowl, cream butter.
Add sugar gradually, beating until light and lemon colored.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Gradually stir in flour and salt.
Add brandy.
In another bowl, mix together (all) raisins, currants, candied orange peel, walnuts, pecans, citron and candied cherries; add to cake mixture, mixing well.
Pour into a greased tube pan (or two small loaf pans).
Bake in oven at 325° for 1 hour or until cake tester inserted to the center comes away clean.
Insert on cake rack.
When cold, sprinkle with brandy; wrap in foil. Store in refrigerator or cool, dry place.
Occasionally loosen foil and spoon brandy over the cake.
Slice thinly.

title: neiman-marcus cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix, 2 eggs and butter.
Batter will be stiff.
Pour in cake pan, then mix powdered sugar, remaining 2 eggs and cream cheese. Pour over first layer.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cake will sink in middle as it cools.

title: bull frogs
directions: Mix all this in large pitcher; sit back and enjoy.

title: mom day's chicken casserole
directions: In a kettle add cream of chicken soup, two cans of water and Good Seasons salad dressing.
Bring to boil.
Remove from heat. Put 1 cup rice on bottom of casserole dish.
Put chicken on top. Cover the chicken and rice with soup mixture.
Cover and put
in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chocolate covered peanut butter balls
directions: Cream the first 4 ingredients well; roll into small balls. Chill for 1 hour.
Melt the remaining ingredients in top of double boiler.
Stick toothpick into ball, then dip into chocolate and place on wax paper.
When all are completed, place in fridge.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Batter will be stiff.
Stir in apples and nuts.
Pour into well buttered tube pan or 2 loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let cake cool 30 minutes before removing from pan.
May use 13 x 9-inch pan; bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cumberland chicken
directions: Dunk chicken breasts in egg and water mixture.
Roll in breading made of crumbs, cheese, sesame seed and parsley.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: fresh blueberry sauce
directions: Combine sugar and cornstarch in a small saucepan.
Stir in water and lemon juice.
Add blueberries; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 to 2 minutes, stirring constantly until clear and thickened.
Serve sauce warm over pancakes, ice cream, etc. Yield:
2 cups.
Contains approximately 10 calories per tablespoon.

title: cajun cabbage
directions: Combine bacon, onion and bell pepper in a large pot in enough water to cook; cook until done.
Add cabbage and tomatoes, salt, pepper, vinegar and cayenne.
Cook for 45 minutes.

title: caramel corn
directions: Boil or simmer brown sugar, oleo and white syrup for 4 to 5 minutes.
Take off stove and add soda.
Pour over corn and stir good.
Put in 225° oven for 1 hour.
Stir 3 or 4 times.
Bake uncovered.

title: best brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt the butter; pour into a large mixing bowl and beat in cocoa and sugar.
When mixture is smooth, beat in eggs, one at a time, then vanilla.
Stir in flour, salt and coconut.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 25 minutes.
Let cool in pan on racks and cut into squares.
Yield: about 30.

title: summer squash
directions: Cook squash until barely tender, cool slightly.
Scoop out centers, leaving a shell.
Mix scooped out squash and mix with remaining ingredients.
Stuff the shells.
Bake at 350° until heated.

title: fudge pie
directions: Beat eggs; add sugar.
Then mix in rest of ingredients.
Pour in pie shell and bake 30 minutes.

title: quick beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Prepare macaroni according to box directions.
Drain Veg-All and partially drain tomatoes.
Mix all ingredients together in large casserole dish.
Top with cheeses. (Or cheese can be mixed in with other ingredients.)
Bake for 20 minutes or until cheese is melted completely at 360°.

title: banana lemon tea bread
directions: In a large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat oleo into creamy consistency and add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Blend in mashed bananas and lemon juice. Add to banana mixture.
Stir in lemon rind.
Place in greased pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potatoes and coconut
directions: Blend and bake in moderate oven until firm.
Use as a vegetable or dessert.

title: marie's carrot spread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
If mixture is too stiff, add a little mayonnaise.
Use as a dip or spread on bread for ribbon sandwiches.

title: apple crisp
directions: Grease 9 x 9-inch pan. Slice apples.
Put 1/2 of apples in pan. Combine all ingredients, except apples and juice.
Sprinkle 1/2 of mixture on apples. Put remaining sliced apples over the dry mixture.
Place remaining apples on top.
Sprinkle remaining sugar mixture on top of apples.
Drizzle apple juice over top.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: Boil chicken, onion, celery and salt in water until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken to cool and debone.
Strain broth.
Reserve 1 cup broth for dough.
Add cream of chicken soup and nutmeg to broth.
Mix well.
Return to heat.
Dough:
Cut shortening into flour and salt.
Beat egg.
Add cooled broth and add to flour to make a firm dough.
Add more flour, if necessary.
Roll dough as thin as possible.
Return chicken to broth.
Add pepper.
Cut dough into desired square or oblong pieces.
Add one at a time to broth and chicken (which has been brought to boiling point).
Add more water and broth if necessary, so they will be a bit soupy.
If too soupy, add a Tbsp. of flour, mixed with a little water.
After adding dumplings, simmer for 20 minutes.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Place butter and vanilla in bowl.
Beat until mixture is smooth, about 2 minutes.
Add gradually the sugar about 30 seconds and continue beating for 1 minute.
Add eggs and beat for 30 seconds.
Stop and scrape bowl.
Sift dry ingredients.
Turn mixer to speed and gradually add dry ingredients.
Beat about 1 minute. Drop by teaspoons on greased baking sheet about 3-inches apart. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes.
Sprinkle with sugar while hot. Makes about 4 dozen cookies.

title: sunday chicken
directions: Cut up fryer. Salt and paprika it. Saute onion and apple in margarine. Add half and half, curry powder and mushroom soup.
Mix well together.
Put pieces of chicken in baking dish and pour mixture over it. Bake for 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serves 4 to 14.

title: chocolate caramel layered bars
directions: While the kids unwrap the caramels, Mom or Dad prepares a 9 x 13-inch pan (grease and flour).
In a large bowl, combine cake mix, melted butter, 1/3 cup evaporated milk and nuts.
Stir by hand until mixture holds together.
Press half of dough into pan.
Bake at 350° for 6 minutes.

title: pennsylvania pot roast
directions: Rub roast with salt, pepper, paprika and flour.
Cook bacon until crisp; drain on absorbent paper, crumble.
Brown roast in baking pan in 3 tablespoons bacon fat.
Add gherkins, onion, garlic, water and tomato sauce.
Bring to a boil; cover and simmer for 2 1/2 hours until tender.
Blend sour cream and pan gravy; heat.
Stir in bacon bits and serve with roast.
Serves 6.

title: mexican bean salad(tasty sandwich high in fiber and low in fat)
directions: Mix vinegar, chili powder and onion powder with mayonnaise in small bowl.
Add beans and celery; mix well.
Soften tortillas in heated frypan for about 1 to 2 minutes.
Turn if necessary.
Place half of the bean filling onto each tortilla.
Top with tomato and lettuce and roll up.
Makes 2 servings.

title: new england salsa
directions: Chop all ingredients that need to be chopped.
In a large, plastic or glass bowl, combine all ingredients, except salt, pepper, garlic and Tabasco.
Stir well.
Add salt, pepper, garlic and Tabasco to taste.
Taste with a tortilla chip, otherwise it does not taste right.
Serve with lots of tortilla chips and company.
Keeps well for one month in a tightly sealed jar.

title: egg and sausage breakfast casserole
directions: Cook and drain sausage, crumble.
Layer muffins, sausage, eggs, mustard and cheese.
You can add other ingredients like onions, peppers, etc.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes until cheese melts.

title: walnut cookies
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients like a pie crust.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup of warm water with 1/2 teaspoon of sugar; then add 1/2 cup evaporated milk and 4 egg yolks to flour mixture.
Add 1/2 cup sugar and beaten egg whites to walnuts.

title: pineapple sour cream pie
directions: Mix pudding and pineapple with juice, sour cream, vanilla and sugar in a deep bowl; beat for one minute on lowest speed.
Pour into a pie shell and chill.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix in blender or stir real good.

title: apple goodie
directions: Place apples in baking dish.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, flour and oatmeal; sprinkle over apples.
Dot very generously with margarine.
Bake at 425° about 40 minutes.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Beat pudding mix and milk; set aside. Beat cream cheese and Cool Whip; add pudding mixture. Drain pineapple, then add to pudding mixture; mix in marshmallows.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: dishpan cookies
directions: Mix the 2 sugars and oil.
Add eggs, vanilla, soda and salt; mix well.
Add flour, oats and the rest of ingredients.

title: enchiladas
directions: Cook meat until brown; drain.
Add onions and Cheddar cheese. Let melt.
Dip corn tortillas in hot grease for 10 seconds.
Drain on paper towel.
Place meat in tortillas and wrap.
Place in baking dish and cover with cheese sauce.
Sprinkle rest of grated cheese on top.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: truckers' beans
directions: In large skillet, saute onions and green pepper until slightly softened.
Push sausage out of casing; brown in same pan.
Drain excess fat.
Combine all ingredients; heat through.
(Or put in large casserole and bake at 400° for 35 to 40 minutes).
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: lazy day cookies
directions: Place 18 graham cookies in a single layer on a cookie sheet. Now combine remaining ingredients.
Blend well and cook, stirring constantly, for 5 minutes or until mixture is thick.
Spread mixture over layer of graham crackers.
Now put 18 crackers over the mixture.
Cover the top layer by combining 1 1/2 cups powdered sugar with vanilla flavoring.
Add just enough milk and melted oleo to give good spreading quality.
Put in refrigerator until cold. Cut in bars.
Tastes like date cookies.

title: pumpkin cake pie
directions: Beat
together	first
seven
ingredients and pour into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.	Empty the yellow cake mix over it, breaking
any
lumps in the mixture.
Pour in melted margarine and sprinkle
the
top	with chopped nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, no	longer.
It
should
be
a
nice, golden brown.
May serve topped with whipped cream if you wish.

title: creamed corn
directions: Put corn, butter, salt and pepper in saucepan.
Heat until warm.
Serve with love.

title: broken glass cake
directions: Dissolve each jello (lemon, cherry and lime) in 1 1/2 cups water and chill.
Crush crackers and mix with 1/2 cup sugar and butter.
Put 1/2 of mix in bottom of oblong dish.
Dissolve plain gelatin in 1/4 cup cold water.
Heat 1 cup pineapple juice to boiling and add to gelatin; let cool.
Whip the cream and add 1/2 cup sugar and vanilla.
Fold into the pineapple juice.
Cut up jello into cubes and fold into whipped cream mixture.
Pour all into cracker lined pan and top with remaining cracker crumbs.

title: orange tapioca salad
directions: Mix jello, pudding and water in saucepan.
Bring to a boil. Boil 2 minutes.
Let cool.
Add Cool Whip; stir well.
Add pineapple (drained well) and oranges (drained well).
Stir well. Ready to eat.

title: chicken soup
directions: Boil chicken for 1 hour.
Cut into bite-sized pieces.
Mix in all ingredients
in the same water that you boiled the chicken in. For dumplings, add more water.
Heat until hot and dumplings have cooked, about 20 to 25 minutes over medium heat (covered).

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Blend sugar, flour and baking powder together.
Mix with eggs, then add butter, milk, vanilla and coconut.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: bacon baked beans
directions: Brown chopped bacon.
Add onions and fry until tender.
Add sugar, vinegar, garlic powder, dry mustard and sausage.
Stir and simmer a few minutes.
Add to beans.
Do not drain grease.
Bake, uncovered, 1 1/2 to 2 hours at 350°.
Freezes very well.
Makes lots!!!

title: nenek's curry
directions: Saute onions and garlic in oil until soft.
Add enough water to make a paste.
Add curry powders and let simmer 10 minutes.
Add potatoes, tofu and chicken seasoning, covering with water.
Cook until potatoes are soft.
Just before serving, add last 2 ingredients.

title: party mix
directions: Place margarine in large glass bowl.
Microwave about 1 minute on High.
Stir in seasoned salt and Worcestershire sauce.
Add Chex and nuts.
Mix well until all pieces are coated.
Microwave 5 1/2 to 6 1/2 minutes on High or until Chex look toasted.
Stir every 2 minutes.
Spread on absorbent paper to cool.
Yield:
3 1/2 cups.

title: squash dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in Pyrex dish.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
After its about done, sprinkle cheese on top and melt.

title: bubble recipe(for large outside bubbles)
directions: *These brands work the best.

title: lazy cook's salad
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients, then add last 3 ingredients and mix together.
Let stand a day or so.

title: caramel nut cake
directions: Have all ingredients at room temperature.
Separate eggs. Beat yolks well.
Combine sugar and baking powder and add to yolks.
Add vanilla and almond extract.
Beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into egg yolk mixture.
Fold in graham cracker crumbs and walnuts and blend well.
Line 2 (9-inch) greased layer pans with wax paper and then pour in mixture.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 35 minutes.
When cool, spread 1 pint of whipped cream between layers and over top of cake.
Pour Butterscotch Sauce over top and let run down sides.
Refrigerate at least 3 hours before serving.
Serves 20.

title: saltless seasoning salt
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Cover and store in a dry place.

title: homemade cinnamon rolls
directions: In a large mixer bowl, combine 1 1/2 cups of the flour and yeast.
Heat the milk, sugar, the 1/4 cup butter and salt just until mixture is warm (120°) and the butter is almost melted, stirring constantly.
Add milk mixture to flour mixture; add eggs. Beat with an electric mixer on low speed for 30 seconds; scrape sides of bowl constantly.
Beat on high speed for 3 minutes.
Using a spoon, stir in as much of the remaining flour as you can (dough will be soft).
Turn dough out onto a lightly floured surface. Knead in enough of the remaining flour to make a moderately soft dough (3 to 5 minutes).
On lightly floured surface, roll half the dough to 12 x 8-inches.
Spread with 3 tablespoons softened butter. Combine brown sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle half over rectangle. Roll up from a short side.
Seal edges.
Make a second roll with remaining dough, butter and sugar mixture.
Slice each dough roll into 8 pieces.
Arrange slices, cut side down, in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Cover; let rise until nearly double (about 1 hour).
Bake rolls in a 350° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Invert at once onto a wire rack.
Cool slightly. Drizzle rolls with Maple Nut glaze or powder sugar glaze.
Serve warm.
Makes 16 rolls.

title: chili sauce
directions: Peel tomatoes and onions; remove seeds from peppers and chop them fine. Stir all together and add salt, sugar, cinnamon, cloves and vinegar. Cook slowly for 45 to 60 minutes or until thick, stirring occasionally. Pour into hot sterilized jars and seal. Makes 4 pints. If desired, add 2 hot red peppers, seeded and chopped.

title: cauliflower in cheese sauce
directions: Cook cauliflower in cup of water.
Sprinkle salt on it and cook until tender, uncovered for 10 minutes.
Use slotted spoon to remove cauliflower.
Reserve cooking water.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Layer 3 pieces of heavy foil crisscross.
Melt butter.
Place potatoes on foil.
Pour butter and cream on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Lay onion slices on top.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 325° for 2 1/2 hours.

title: sausage cheese grits casserole
directions: Bring salted water to boil.
Slowly add quick cooking grits (not instant).
Return to boil, cover, reduce heat and cook 3 to 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat and add cheese; stir until melted. Add milk, butter, Worcestershire sauce and garlic salt.
Mix well.
Beat egg in small bowl.
Add 1 tablespoon grits mixture until blended and add back to grits.
Spoon half of grits into an 8-inch square baking dish, top with one pound of cooked and drained sausage and cover with remaining grits.
Cover and chill 8 hours.

title: yesteryears' cornbread
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt; stir in corn meal. Add eggs, milk and shortening; beat until just smooth.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.
I used the cornbread recipe in 1936-1943.
At that time, there was a grist mill across Highway 30.
The man delivered the meal.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour half hamburger in casserole dish.
Add cubed potatoes, chopped onion and bell pepper.
Add remainder of hamburger.
Spread 1 can cream of celery soup evenly over hamburger.
Cook about 30 minutes at 350°. May add cheese to top and brown.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Peel and slice peaches.
Put in crust. Bring sugar, water, cornstarch and salt to a boil.
Add Jell-O to boiled mixture. Pour over peaches and refrigerate.
